{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["40-MAT-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "MAT"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Matti \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Good News According to Matti \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Matti \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Mat \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Good News According to \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Matti \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 1:1"}, "The book of the genealogy of Al Masih Isa,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Messiah (Hebrew) and ChristGreek both mean \u201cAnointed\nOne\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " the son of Dawood, the son of Ibrahim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 1:2"}, "Ibrahim became the father of Is\u1e25\u0101q. Is\u1e25\u0101q became the father of Yaqub. Yaqub became the father of Judah and his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 1:3"}, "Judah became the father of Perez and Zerah by Tamar. Perez became the father of Hezron. Hezron became the father of Ram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 1:4"}, "Ram became the father of Amminadab. Amminadab became the father of Nahshon. Nahshon became the father of Salmon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 1:5"}, "Salmon became the father of Boaz by Rahab. Boaz became the father of Obed by Ruth. Obed became the father of Jesse.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 1:6"}, "Jesse became the father of King Dawood. Dawood became the father of Sulaiman by her who had been Uriah\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 1:7"}, "Sulaiman became the father of Rehoboam. Rehoboam became the father of Abijah. Abijah became the father of Asa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 1:8"}, "Asa became the father of Jehoshaphat. Jehoshaphat became the father of Joram. Joram became the father of Uzziah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 1:9"}, "Uzziah became the father of Jotham. Jotham became the father of Ahaz. Ahaz became the father of Hezekiah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 1:10"}, "Hezekiah became the father of Manasseh. Manasseh became the father of Amon. Amon became the father of Josiah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 1:11"}, "Josiah became the father of Jechoniah and his brothers, at the time of the exile to Babylon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 1:12"}, "After the exile to Babylon, Jechoniah became the father of Shealtiel. Shealtiel became the father of Zerubbabel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 1:13"}, "Zerubbabel became the father of Abiud. Abiud became the father of Eliakim. Eliakim became the father of Azor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 1:14"}, "Azor became the father of Zadok. Zadok became the father of Achim. Achim became the father of Eliud.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 1:15"}, "Eliud became the father of Eleazar. Eleazar became the father of Matthan. Matthan became the father of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 1:16"}, "Yaqub became the father of Yusuf, the husband of Maryam, from whom was born\nIsa,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cIsa\u201d means \u201cSalvation\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " who is called Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 1:17"}, "So all the generations from Ibrahim to Dawood are fourteen generations; from Dawood to the exile to Babylon fourteen\ngenerations; and from the carrying away to Babylon to the Masih, fourteen generations.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 1:18"}, "Now the birth of Al Masih Isa was like this: After his mother, Maryam, was engaged to Yusuf, before they came together,\nshe was found pregnant by the Holy Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 1:19"}, "Yusuf, her husband, being a righteous man, and not willing to make her a public example, intended to put her away\nsecretly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 1:20"}, "But when he thought about these things, behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:20\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying, \u201cYusuf, son of Dawood, don\u2019t be afraid to take to\nyourself Maryam, your wife, for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 1:21"}, "She shall give birth to a son. You shall call his name Isa,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cIsa\u201d means \u201cSalvation\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " for it is he who shall save his people from their sins.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 1:22"}, "Now all this has happened that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 1:23"}, "\u201cBehold, the virgin shall be with child, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall give birth to a son. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They shall call his name Immanuel;\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which is, being interpreted, \u201cAllah with us.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n7:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 1:24"}, "Yusuf arose from his sleep, and did as the angel of the Lord commanded him, and took his wife to himself;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 1:25"}, "and didn\u2019t know her sexually until she had given birth to her firstborn son. He named him Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 2:1"}, "Now when Isa was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of King Herod, behold, wise\nmen", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cwise men\u201d (magoi) can also mean teachers, scientists, physicians, astrologers, seers,\ninterpreters of dreams, or sorcerers."]}], "caller": "+"}, " from the east came to Jerusalem, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 2:2"}, "\u201cWhere is he who is born King of the Jews? For we saw his star in the east, and have come to worship him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 2:3"}, "When King Herod heard it, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 2:4"}, "Gathering together all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he asked them where the Masih would be born.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 2:5"}, "They said to him, \u201cIn Bethlehem of Judea, for this is written through the prophet,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 2:6"}, "\u2018You Bethlehem, land of Judah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["are in no way least amongst the princes of Judah: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for out of you shall come a governor, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who shall shepherd my people, Israel.\u2019\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Micah\n5:2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 2:7"}, "Then Herod secretly called the wise men, and learnt from them exactly what time the star appeared.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 2:8"}, "He sent them to Bethlehem, and said, \u201cGo and search diligently for the young child. When you have found him, bring me\nword, so that I also may come and worship him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 2:9"}, "They, having heard the king, went their way; and behold, the star, which they saw in the east, went before them, until it\ncame and stood over where the young child was. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 2:10"}, "When they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceedingly great joy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 2:11"}, "They came into the house and saw the young child with Maryam, his mother, and they fell down and worshipped him. Opening\ntheir treasures, they offered to him gifts: gold, frankincense, and myrrh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 2:12"}, "Being warned in a dream not to return to Herod, they went back to their own country another way.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 2:13"}, "Now when they had departed, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to Yusuf in a dream, saying, \u201cArise and take the young\nchild and his mother, and flee into Egypt, and stay there until I tell you, for Herod will seek the young child to destroy\nhim.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 2:14"}, "He arose and took the young child and his mother by night, and departed into Egypt,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 2:15"}, "and was there until the death of Herod; that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the Lord through the prophet,\nsaying, \u201cOut of Egypt I called my son.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Hosea 11:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 2:16"}, "Then Herod, when he saw that he was mocked by the wise men, was exceedingly angry, and sent out, and killed all the male\nchildren who were in Bethlehem and in all the surrounding countryside, from two years old and under, according to the exact\ntime which he had learnt from the wise men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 2:17"}, "Then that which was spoken by Jeremiah the prophet was fulfilled, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 2:18"}, "\u201cA voice was heard in Ramah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lamentation, weeping and great mourning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Rachel weeping for her children; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["she wouldn\u2019t be comforted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because they are no more.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Jeremiah 31:15"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 2:19"}, "But when Herod was dead, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Yusuf in Egypt, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 2:20"}, "\u201cArise and take the young child and his mother, and go into the land of Israel, for those who sought the young child\u2019s\nlife are dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 2:21"}, "He arose and took the young child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 2:22"}, "But when he heard that Archelaus was reigning over Judea in the place of his father, Herod, he was afraid to go there.\nBeing warned in a dream, he withdrew into the region of Galilee,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 2:23"}, "and came and lived in a city called Nazareth; that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through the prophets that he\nwill be called a Nazarene. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 3:1"}, "In those days, Yahya the Baptiser came, preaching in the wilderness of Judea, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 3:2"}, "\u201cRepent, for the Kingdom of Heaven is at hand!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 3:3"}, "For this is he who was spoken of by Isaiah the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe voice of one crying in the wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["make the way of the Lord ready! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Make his paths straight!\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 40:3"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 3:4"}, "Now Yahya himself wore clothing made of camel\u2019s hair, with a leather belt around his waist. His food was locusts and wild\nhoney. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 3:5"}, "Then people from Jerusalem, all of Judea, and all the region around the Jordan went out to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 3:6"}, "They were baptised by him in the Jordan, confessing their sins.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 3:7"}, "But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming for his baptism, he said to them, \u201cYou offspring of vipers, who\nwarned you to flee from the wrath to come? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 3:8"}, "Therefore produce fruit worthy of repentance! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 3:9"}, "Don\u2019t think to yourselves, \u2018We have Ibrahim for our father,\u2019 for I tell you that Allah is able to raise up children to\nIbrahim from these stones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 3:10"}, "\u201cEven now the axe lies at the root of the trees. Therefore every tree that doesn\u2019t produce good fruit is cut down, and\ncast into the fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 3:11"}, "I indeed baptise you in water for repentance, but he who comes after me is mightier than I, whose sandals I am not worthy\nto carry. He will baptise you in the Holy Spirit.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU add \u201cand with fire\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 3:12"}, "His winnowing fork is in his hand, and he will thoroughly cleanse his threshing floor. He will gather his wheat into the\nbarn, but the chaff he will burn up with unquenchable fire.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 3:13"}, "Then Isa came from Galilee to the Jordan", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["i.e., the Jordan\nRiver"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to Yuhanna, to be baptised by him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 3:14"}, "But Yahya would have hindered him, saying, \u201cI need to be baptised by you, and you come to me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 3:15"}, "But Isa, answering, said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAllow it now, for this is the fitting way for us to fulfil all\nrighteousness.\u201d"]}, " Then he allowed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 3:16"}, "Isa, when he was baptised, went up directly from the water: and behold, the heavens were opened to him. He saw the Spirit\nof Allah descending as a dove, and coming on him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 3:17"}, "Behold, a voice out of the heavens said, \u201cThis is my beloved Son, with whom I am well pleased.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 4:1"}, "Then Isa was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the Iblis.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 4:2"}, "When he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was hungry afterward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 4:3"}, "The tempter came and said to him, \u201cIf you are the Son of Allah, command that these stones become bread.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 4:4"}, "But he answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt is written, \u2018Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth\nof Allah.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 8:3"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 4:5"}, "Then the Iblis took him into the holy city. He set him on the pinnacle of the temple,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 4:6"}, "and said to him, \u201cIf you are the Son of Allah, throw yourself down, for it is written, \u2018He will command his angels\nconcerning you.\u2019 and, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018On their hands they will bear you up, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that you don\u2019t dash your foot against a stone.\u2019\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:6\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 91:11-12 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 4:7"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAgain, it is written, \u2018You shall not test the Lord, your\nAllah.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 6:16"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 4:8"}, "Again, the Iblis took him to an exceedingly high mountain, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world, and their glory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 4:9"}, "He said to him, \u201cI will give you all of these things, if you will fall down and worship me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 4:10"}, "Then Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGet behind me,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:10\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU read \u201cGo away\u201d instead of \u201cGet behind me\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Iblis! For it is written, \u2018You shall worship Allah your Lord,\nand you shall serve him only.\u2019\u201d"]}, " ", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy\n6:13"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 4:11"}, "Then the Iblis left him, and behold, angels came and served him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 4:12"}, "Now when Isa heard that Yahya was delivered up, he withdrew into Galilee.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 4:13"}, "Leaving Nazareth, he came and lived in Capernaum, which is by the sea, in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 4:14"}, "that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 4:15"}, "\u201cThe land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["towards the sea, beyond the Jordan, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Galilee of the Gentiles, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 4:16"}, "the people who sat in darkness saw a great light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to those who sat in the region and shadow of death, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to them light has dawned.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 9:1-2"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 4:17"}, "From that time, Isa began to preach, and to say, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cRepent! For the Kingdom of Heaven is at\nhand.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 4:18"}, "Walking by the sea of Galilee, he", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cIsa\u201d instead of \u201che\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " saw two brothers: Shima\u2019un, who is called Peter, and Andreas, his brother, casting a net into the sea; for they were\nfishermen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 4:19"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCome after me, and I will make you fishers for\nmen.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 4:20"}, "They immediately left their nets and followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 4:21"}, "Going on from there, he saw two other brothers, Yaqub the son of Zebedee, and Yuhanna his brother, in the boat with\nZebedee their father, mending their nets. He called them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 4:22"}, "They immediately left the boat and their father, and followed him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 4:23"}, "Isa went about in all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, preaching the Good News of the Kingdom, and healing every\ndisease and every sickness amongst the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 4:24"}, "The report about him went out into all Syria. They brought to him all who were sick, afflicted with various diseases and\ntorments, possessed with demons, epileptics, and paralytics; and he healed them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 4:25"}, "Great multitudes from Galilee, Decapolis, Jerusalem, Judea and from beyond the Jordan followed him.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 5:1"}, "Seeing the multitudes, he went up onto the mountain. When he had sat down, his disciples came to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 5:2"}, "He opened his mouth and taught them, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 5:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBlessed are the poor in spirit,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n57:15; 66:2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 5:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are those who mourn,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall be comforted."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n61:2; 66:10,13"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 5:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are the gentle,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall inherit the earth."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\nland."]}], "caller": "+"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 37:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 5:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are those who hunger and thirst after righteousness,\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall be filled."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 5:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are the merciful,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall obtain mercy."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 5:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are the pure in heart,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall see Allah."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 5:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are the peacemakers,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they shall be called children of Allah."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 5:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed are those who have been persecuted for righteousness\u2019 sake,\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 5:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBlessed are you when people reproach you, persecute you, and say all kinds of evil against you falsely, for my\nsake. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 5:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Rejoice, and be exceedingly glad, for great is your reward in heaven. For that is how they persecuted the prophets\nwho were before you. "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 5:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou are the salt of the earth, but if the salt has lost its flavour, with what will it be salted? It is then good\nfor nothing, but to be cast out and trodden under the feet of men.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 5:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You are the light of the world. A city located on a hill can\u2019t be hidden.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 5:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Neither do you light a lamp, and put it under a measuring basket, but on a stand; and it shines to all who are in\nthe house. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 5:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Even so, let your light shine before men; that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father who is in\nheaven."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 5:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t think that I came to destroy the law or the prophets. I didn\u2019t come to destroy, but to fulfil.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 5:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For most certainly, I tell you, until heaven and earth pass away, not even one smallest\nletter"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, iota"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["or one tiny pen\nstroke"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, serif"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["shall in any way pass away from the law, until all things are accomplished.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 5:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever, therefore, shall break one of these least commandments, and teach others to do so, shall be called least in\nthe Kingdom of Heaven; but whoever shall do and teach them shall be called great in the Kingdom of Heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 5:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For I tell you that unless your righteousness exceeds that of the scribes and Pharisees, there is no way you will\nenter into the Kingdom of Heaven."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 5:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou have heard that it was said to the ancient ones, \u2018You shall not\nmurder;\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:13"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and \u2018Whoever murders will be in danger of the judgement.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 5:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you that everyone who is angry with his brother without a cause\n"]}, " ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits \u201cwithout a cause\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["will be in danger of the judgement. Whoever says to his brother,\n\u2018Raca!\u2019 "]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cRaca\u201d is an Aramaic insult, related to the word for \u201cempty\u201d and conveying the idea of\nempty-headedness."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["will be in danger of the council. Whoever says, \u2018You fool!\u2019 will be in danger of the fire of\nGehenna."]}, " ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 5:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf therefore you are offering your gift at the altar, and there remember that your brother has anything against\nyou, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 5:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["leave your gift there before the altar, and go your way. First be reconciled to your brother, and then come and\noffer your gift. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 5:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Agree with your adversary quickly, while you are with him on the way; lest perhaps the prosecutor deliver you to the\njudge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and you be cast into prison.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 5:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, you shall by no means get out of there, until you have paid the last\npenny."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, kodrantes. A kodrantes was a small copper coin worth about 2 lepta (widow\u2019s mites)\u2014not\nenough to buy very much of anything."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 5:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou have heard that it was said, "]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cto the\nancients\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018You shall not commit adultery;\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:27\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 5:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but I tell you that everyone who gazes at a woman to lust after her has committed adultery with her already in his\nheart. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 5:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your right eye causes you to stumble, pluck it out and throw it away from you. For it is more profitable for you\nthat one of your members should perish, than for your whole body to be cast into\nGehenna."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 5:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your right hand causes you to stumble, cut it off, and throw it away from you. For it is more profitable for you\nthat one of your members should perish, than for your whole body to be cast into\nGehenna."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 5:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt was also said, \u2018Whoever shall put away his wife, let him give her a writing of\ndivorce,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 24:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 5:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but I tell you that whoever puts away his wife, except for the cause of sexual immorality, makes her an adulteress;\nand whoever marries her when she is put away commits adultery."]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 5:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAgain you have heard that it was said to the ancient ones, \u2018You shall not make false vows, but shall perform to the\nLord your vows,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Numbers 30:2; Deuteronomy\n23:21; Ecclesiastes 5:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 5:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but I tell you, don\u2019t swear at all: neither by heaven, for it is the throne of Allah;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 5:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["nor by the earth, for it is the footstool of his feet; nor by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the great King.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 5:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Neither shall you swear by your head, for you can\u2019t make one hair white or black.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 5:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But let your \u2018Yes\u2019 be \u2018Yes\u2019 and your \u2018No\u2019 be \u2018No.\u2019 Whatever is more than these is of the evil\none."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 5:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou have heard that it was said, \u2018An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a\ntooth.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 21:24; Leviticus 24:20; Deuteronomy\n19:21"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 5:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you, don\u2019t resist him who is evil; but whoever strikes you on your right cheek, turn to him the other\nalso. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 5:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If anyone sues you to take away your coat, let him have your cloak also.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 5:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever compels you to go one mile, go with him two. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 5:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Give to him who asks you, and don\u2019t turn away him who desires to borrow from\nyou."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 5:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou have heard that it was said, \u2018You shall love your neighbour\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:43 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 19:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and hate your enemy.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:43 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["not in the Bible, but see Qumran Manual of Discipline Ix,\n21-26"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 5:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you, love your enemies, bless those who curse you, do good to those who hate you, and pray for those who\nmistreat you and persecute you, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 5:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["that you may be children of your Father who is in heaven. For he makes his sun to rise on the evil and the good, and\nsends rain on the just and the unjust. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 5:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For if you love those who love you, what reward do you have? Don\u2019t even the tax collectors do the same?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 5:47"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If you only greet your friends, what more do you do than others? Don\u2019t even the tax\ncollectors"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cGentiles\u201d instead of \u201ctax\ncollectors\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["do the same? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 5:48"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore you shall be perfect, just as your Father in heaven is\nperfect."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 6:1"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBe careful that you don\u2019t do your charitable giving"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cacts of righteousness\u201d instead of \u201ccharitable\ngiving\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["before men, to be seen by them, or else you have no reward from your Father who is in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 6:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore when you do merciful deeds, don\u2019t sound a trumpet before yourself, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues\nand in the streets, that they may get glory from men. Most certainly I tell you, they have received their reward.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 6:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when you do merciful deeds, don\u2019t let your left hand know what your right hand does,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 6:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["so that your merciful deeds may be in secret, then your Father who sees in secret will reward you\nopenly."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 6:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen you pray, you shall not be as the hypocrites, for they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and in the\ncorners of the streets, that they may be seen by men. Most certainly, I tell you, they have received their reward.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 6:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you, when you pray, enter into your inner room, and having shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret,\nand your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 6:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["In praying, don\u2019t use vain repetitions, as the Gentiles do; for they think that they will be heard for their much\nspeaking. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 6:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore don\u2019t be like them, for your Father knows what things you need, before you ask him.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 6:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Pray like this: \u2018Our Father in heaven, may your name be kept holy.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 6:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Let your Kingdom come. Let your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 6:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Give us today our daily bread. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 6:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Forgive us our debts, as we also forgive our debtors.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 6:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Bring us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one. For yours is the Kingdom, the power, and the glory\nforever. Amen.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits \u201cFor yours is the Kingdom, the power, and the glory forever.\nAmen.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 6:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor if you forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 6:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if you don\u2019t forgive men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your\ntrespasses."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 6:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMoreover when you fast, don\u2019t be like the hypocrites, with sad faces. For they disfigure their faces, that they may\nbe seen by men to be fasting. Most certainly I tell you, they have received their reward.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 6:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you, when you fast, anoint your head, and wash your face;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 6:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["so that you are not seen by men to be fasting, but by your Father who is in secret, and your Father, who sees in\nsecret, will reward you. "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 6:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t lay up treasures for yourselves on the earth, where moth and rust consume, and where thieves break through\nand steal; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 6:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust consume, and where thieves don\u2019t break\nthrough and steal; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 6:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 6:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe lamp of the body is the eye. If therefore your eye is sound, your whole body will be full of light.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 6:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if your eye is evil, your whole body will be full of darkness. If therefore the light that is in you is\ndarkness, how great is the darkness! "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 6:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNo one can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and love the other; or else he will be devoted to one\nand despise the other. You can\u2019t serve both Allah and Mammon. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 6:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore I tell you, don\u2019t be anxious for your life: what you will eat, or what you will drink; nor yet for your\nbody, what you will wear. Isn\u2019t life more than food, and the body more than clothing?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 6:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["See the birds of the sky, that they don\u2019t sow, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns. Your heavenly Father\nfeeds them. Aren\u2019t you of much more value than they?"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 6:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhich of you, by being anxious, can add one moment"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, cubit"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["to his lifespan? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 6:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow. They don\u2019t toil, neither do\nthey spin, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 6:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["yet I tell you that even Sulaiman in all his glory was not dressed like one of these.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 6:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if Allah so clothes the grass of the field, which today exists, and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, won\u2019t he\nmuch more clothe you, you of little faith?"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 6:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTherefore don\u2019t be anxious, saying, \u2018What will we eat?\u2019, \u2018What will we drink?\u2019 or, \u2018With what will we be clothed?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 6:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Gentiles seek after all these things; for your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 6:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But seek first Allah\u2019s Kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things will be given to you as well.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 6:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore don\u2019t be anxious for tomorrow, for tomorrow will be anxious for itself. Each day\u2019s own evil is\nsufficient."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 7:1"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t judge, so that you won\u2019t be judged. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 7:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For with whatever judgement you judge, you will be judged; and with whatever measure you measure, it will be measured\nto you. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 7:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Why do you see the speck that is in your brother\u2019s eye, but don\u2019t consider the beam that is in your own eye?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 7:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or how will you tell your brother, \u2018Let me remove the speck from your eye;\u2019 and behold, the beam is in your own eye?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 7:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You hypocrite! First remove the beam out of your own eye, and then you can see clearly to remove the speck out of\nyour brother\u2019s eye."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 7:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t give that which is holy to the dogs, neither throw your pearls before the pigs, lest perhaps they trample them\nunder their feet, and turn and tear you to pieces."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 7:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAsk, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 7:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be opened.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 7:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or who is there amongst you, who, if his son asks him for bread, will give him a stone?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 7:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or if he asks for a fish, who will give him a serpent?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 7:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father who is in\nheaven give good things to those who ask him! "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 7:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore whatever you desire for men to do to you, you shall also do to them; for this is the law and the\nprophets."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 7:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEnter in by the narrow gate; for wide is the gate and broad is the way that leads to destruction, and many are\nthose who enter in by it. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 7:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["How"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cBecause\u201d instead of\n\u201cHow\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["narrow is the gate, and restricted is the way that leads to life! Few are those who find\nit."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 7:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBeware of false prophets, who come to you in sheep\u2019s clothing, but inwardly are ravening wolves.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 7:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["By their fruits you will know them. Do you gather grapes from thorns, or figs from thistles?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 7:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Even so, every good tree produces good fruit; but the corrupt tree produces evil fruit.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 7:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["A good tree can\u2019t produce evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree produce good fruit.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 7:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Every tree that doesn\u2019t grow good fruit is cut down, and thrown into the fire.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 7:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore by their fruits you will know them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 7:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Not everyone who says to me, \u2018Lord, Lord,\u2019 will enter into the Kingdom of Heaven; but he who does the will of my\nFather who is in heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 7:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Many will tell me in that day, \u2018Lord, Lord, didn\u2019t we prophesy in your name, in your name cast out demons, and in\nyour name do many mighty works?\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 7:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then I will tell them, \u2018I never knew you. Depart from me, you who work\niniquity.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 7:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEveryone therefore who hears these words of mine, and does them, I will liken him to a wise man, who built his\nhouse on a rock. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 7:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The rain came down, the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat on that house; and it didn\u2019t fall, for it was\nfounded on the rock. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 7:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Everyone who hears these words of mine, and doesn\u2019t do them will be like a foolish man, who built his house on the\nsand. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 7:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The rain came down, the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat on that house; and it fell\u2014and great was its\nfall.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 7:28"}, "When Isa had finished saying these things, the multitudes were astonished at his teaching,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 7:29"}, "for he taught them with authority, and not like the scribes.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 8:1"}, "When he came down from the mountain, great multitudes followed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 8:2"}, "Behold, a leper came to him and worshipped him, saying, \u201cLord, if you want to, you can make me clean.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 8:3"}, "Isa stretched out his hand, and touched him, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI want to. Be made\nclean.\u201d"]}, " Immediately his leprosy was cleansed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 8:4"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSee that you tell nobody, but go, show yourself to the priest, and offer the gift that Musa\ncommanded, as a testimony to them.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 8:5"}, "When he came into Capernaum, a centurion came to him, asking him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 8:6"}, "and saying, \u201cLord, my servant lies in the house paralysed, grievously tormented.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 8:7"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI will come and heal him.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 8:8"}, "The centurion answered, \u201cLord, I\u2019m not worthy for you to come under my roof. Just say the word, and my servant will be\nhealed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 8:9"}, "For I am also a man under authority, having under myself soldiers. I tell this one, \u2018Go,\u2019 and he goes; and tell another,\n\u2018Come,\u2019 and he comes; and tell my servant, \u2018Do this,\u2019 and he does it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 8:10"}, "When Isa heard it, he marvelled, and said to those who followed,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, I haven\u2019t found so great a faith, not even in Israel.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 8:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I tell you that many will come from the east and the west, and will sit down with Ibrahim, Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Yaqub in the\nKingdom of Heaven, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 8:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but the children of the Kingdom will be thrown out into the outer darkness. There will be weeping and gnashing of\nteeth.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 8:13"}, "Isa said to the centurion, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo your way. Let it be done for you as you have\nbelieved.\u201d"]}, " His servant was healed in that hour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 8:14"}, "When Isa came into Peter\u2019s house, he saw his wife\u2019s mother lying sick with a fever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 8:15"}, "He touched her hand, and the fever left her. She got up and served him.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cthem\u201d instead of \u201chim\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 8:16"}, "When evening came, they brought to him many possessed with demons. He cast out the spirits with a word, and healed all\nwho were sick; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 8:17"}, "that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying, \u201cHe took our infirmities, and bore our\ndiseases.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["8:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 53:4 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 8:18"}, "Now when Isa saw great multitudes around him, he gave the order to depart to the other side.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 8:19"}, "A scribe came, and said to him, \u201cTeacher, I will follow you wherever you go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 8:20"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe foxes have holes, and the birds of the sky have nests, but the Son of Man has nowhere to lay\nhis head.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 8:21"}, "Another of his disciples said to him, \u201cLord, allow me first to go and bury my father.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 8:22"}, "But Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFollow me, and leave the dead to bury their own\ndead.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 8:23"}, "When he got into a boat, his disciples followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 8:24"}, "Behold, a violent storm came up on the sea, so much that the boat was covered with the waves, but he was asleep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 8:25"}, "They came to him, and woke him up, saying, \u201cSave us, Lord! We are dying!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 8:26"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy are you fearful, O you of little faith?\u201d\n"]}, " Then he got up, rebuked the wind and the sea, and there was a great calm.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 8:27"}, "The men marvelled, saying, \u201cWhat kind of man is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 8:28"}, "When he came to the other side, into the country of the Gergesenes,\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cGadarenes\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " two people possessed by demons met him there, coming out of the tombs, exceedingly\nfierce, so that nobody could pass that way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 8:29"}, "Behold, they cried out, saying, \u201cWhat do we have to do with you, Isa, Son of Allah? Have you come here to torment us\nbefore the time?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 8:30"}, "Now there was a herd of many pigs feeding far away from them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 8:31"}, "The demons begged him, saying, \u201cIf you cast us out, permit us to go away into the herd of pigs.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 8:32"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They came out, and went into the herd of pigs: and behold, the whole herd of pigs rushed down the cliff into the sea, and\ndied in the water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 8:33"}, "Those who fed them fled, and went away into the city, and told everything, including what happened to those who were\npossessed with demons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 8:34"}, "Behold, all the city came out to meet Isa. When they saw him, they begged that he would depart from their borders.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 9:1"}, "He entered into a boat, and crossed over, and came into his own city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 9:2"}, "Behold, they brought to him a man who was paralysed, lying on a bed. Isa, seeing their faith, said to the paralytic,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSon, cheer up! Your sins are forgiven you.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 9:3"}, "Behold, some of the scribes said to themselves, \u201cThis man blasphemes.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 9:4"}, "Isa, knowing their thoughts, said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you think evil in your hearts?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 9:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For which is easier, to say, \u2018Your sins are forgiven;\u2019 or to say, \u2018Get up, and walk?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 9:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive\nsins-\u201d"]}, " (then he said to the paralytic), ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGet up, and take up your mat, and go to your\nhouse.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 9:7"}, "He arose and departed to his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 9:8"}, "But when the multitudes saw it, they marvelled and glorified Allah, who had given such authority to men.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 9:9"}, "As Isa passed by from there, he saw a man called Matti sitting at the tax collection office. He said to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFollow me.\u201d"]}, " He got up and followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 9:10"}, "As he sat in the house, behold, many tax collectors and sinners came and sat down with Isa and his disciples.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 9:11"}, "When the Pharisees saw it, they said to his disciples, \u201cWhy does your teacher eat with tax collectors and sinners?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 9:12"}, "When Isa heard it, he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThose who are healthy have no need for a physician, but those who are sick do.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 9:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you go and learn what this means: \u2018I desire mercy, and not\nsacrifice,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["9:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Hosea 6:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to\nrepentance.\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits \u201cto repentance\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 9:14"}, "Then Yahya\u2019s disciples came to him, saying, \u201cWhy do we and the Pharisees fast often, but your disciples don\u2019t fast?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 9:15"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCan the friends of the bridegroom mourn, as long as the bridegroom is with them? But the days will\ncome when the bridegroom will be taken away from them, and then they will fast.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 9:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["No one puts a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment; for the patch would tear away from the garment, and a worse\nhole is made. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 9:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Neither do people put new wine into old wine skins, or else the skins would burst, and the wine be spilled, and the\nskins ruined. No, they put new wine into fresh wine skins, and both are\npreserved.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 9:18"}, "While he told these things to them, behold, a ruler came and worshipped him, saying, \u201cMy daughter has just died, but come\nand lay your hand on her, and she will live.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 9:19"}, "Isa got up and followed him, as did his disciples. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 9:20"}, "Behold, a woman who had a discharge of blood for twelve years came behind him, and touched the\nfringe", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of his garment; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 9:21"}, "for she said within herself, \u201cIf I just touch his garment, I will be made well.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 9:22"}, "But Isa, turning around and seeing her, said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDaughter, cheer up! Your faith has made you\nwell.\u201d"]}, " And the woman was made well from that hour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 9:23"}, "When Isa came into the ruler\u2019s house, and saw the flute players, and the crowd in noisy disorder,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 9:24"}, "he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMake room, because the girl isn\u2019t dead, but\nsleeping.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They were ridiculing him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 9:25"}, "But when the crowd was put out, he entered in, took her by the hand, and the girl arose.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 9:26"}, "The report of this went out into all that land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 9:27"}, "As Isa passed by from there, two blind men followed him, calling out and saying, \u201cHave mercy on us, son of Dawood!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 9:28"}, "When he had come into the house, the blind men came to him. Isa said to them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDo you believe that I am able to do this?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They told him, \u201cYes, Lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 9:29"}, "Then he touched their eyes, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAccording to your faith be it done to\nyou.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 9:30"}, "Their eyes were opened. Isa strictly commanded them, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSee that no one knows about this.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 9:31"}, "But they went out and spread abroad his fame in all that land.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 9:32"}, "As they went out, behold, a mute man who was demon possessed was brought to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 9:33"}, "When the demon was cast out, the mute man spoke. The multitudes marvelled, saying, \u201cNothing like this has ever been seen\nin Israel!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 9:34"}, "But the Pharisees said, \u201cBy the prince of the demons, he casts out demons.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 9:35"}, "Isa went about all the cities and the villages, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the Good News of the Kingdom,\nand healing every disease and every sickness amongst the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 9:36"}, "But when he saw the multitudes, he was moved with compassion for them, because they were\nharassed", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cweary\u201d instead of \u201charassed\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and scattered, like sheep without a shepherd. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 9:37"}, "Then he said to his disciples, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe harvest indeed is plentiful, but the labourers are few.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 9:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Pray therefore that the Lord of the harvest will send out labourers into his\nharvest.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 10:1"}, "He called to himself his twelve disciples, and gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal\nevery disease and every sickness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 10:2"}, "Now the names of the twelve apostles are these. The first, Shima\u2019un, who is called Peter; Andreas, his brother; Yaqub the\nson of Zebedee; Yuhanna, his brother; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 10:3"}, "Philip; Bar-Talmai; Tau\u2019ma; Matti the tax collector; Yaqub the son of Alphaeus; Lebbaeus, who was also\ncalled", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits \u201cLebbaeus, who was also called\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Theudas;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 10:4"}, "Shima\u2019un the Canaanite; and Yehuda Iscariot, who also betrayed him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 10:5"}, "Isa sent these twelve out, and commanded them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t go amongst the Gentiles, and don\u2019t enter into any city\nof the Samaritans. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 10:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Rather, go to the lost sheep of the house of Israel. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 10:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["As you go, preach, saying, \u2018The Kingdom of Heaven is at hand!\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 10:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201craise the\ndead,\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and cast out demons. Freely you received, so freely give.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 10:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t take any gold, silver, or brass in your money belts.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 10:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Take no bag for your journey, neither two coats, nor sandals, nor staff: for the labourer is worthy of his food.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 10:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Into whatever city or village you enter, find out who in it is worthy; and stay there until you go on.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 10:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["As you enter into the household, greet it. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 10:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If the household is worthy, let your peace come on it, but if it isn\u2019t worthy, let your peace return to you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 10:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever doesn\u2019t receive you, nor hear your words, as you go out of that house or that city, shake the dust off your\nfeet. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 10:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgement than\nfor that city."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 10:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, I send you out as sheep amongst wolves. Therefore be wise as serpents, and harmless as doves.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 10:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But beware of men: for they will deliver you up to councils, and in their synagogues they will scourge you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 10:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Yes, and you will be brought before governors and kings for my sake, for a testimony to them and to the nations.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 10:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when they deliver you up, don\u2019t be anxious how or what you will say, for it will be given you in that hour what\nyou will say. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 10:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For it is not you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father who speaks in\nyou."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 10:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBrother will deliver up brother to death, and the father his child. Children will rise up against parents, and\ncause them to be put to death. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 10:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You will be hated by all men for my name\u2019s sake, but he who endures to the end will be saved.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 10:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when they persecute you in this city, flee into the next, for most certainly I tell you, you will not have gone\nthrough the cities of Israel until the Son of Man has come."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 10:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cA disciple is not above his teacher, nor a servant above his lord.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 10:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It is enough for the disciple that he be like his teacher, and the servant like his lord. If they have called the\nmaster of the house Beelzebul,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Literally, Lord of the Flies, or the\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["how much more those of his household! "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 10:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore don\u2019t be afraid of them, for there is nothing covered that will not be revealed; and hidden that will not\nbe known. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 10:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What I tell you in the darkness, speak in the light; and what you hear whispered in the ear, proclaim on the\nhousetops. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 10:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t be afraid of those who kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul. Rather, fear him who is able to\ndestroy both soul and body in Gehenna."]}, " ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\nHell."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 10:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAren\u2019t two sparrows sold for an assarion coin?"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["An assarion is a small coin worth one tenth of a drachma or a sixteenth of a denarius. An assarion is\napproximately the wages of one half hour of agricultural labour."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Not one of them falls on the ground apart from your Father\u2019s will,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 10:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but the very hairs of your head are all numbered. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 10:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore don\u2019t be afraid. You are of more value than many sparrows.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 10:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Everyone therefore who confesses me before men, I will also confess him before my Father who is in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 10:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But whoever denies me before men, I will also deny him before my Father who is in\nheaven."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 10:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t think that I came to send peace on the earth. I didn\u2019t come to send peace, but a sword.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 10:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For I came to set a man at odds against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against\nher mother-in-law. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 10:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["A man\u2019s foes will be those of his own household."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Micah 7:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 10:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me; and he who loves son or daughter more than me isn\u2019t\nworthy of me. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 10:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who doesn\u2019t take his cross and follow after me, isn\u2019t worthy of me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 10:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who seeks his life will lose it; and he who loses his life for my sake will find it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 10:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who receives you receives me, and he who receives me receives him who sent me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 10:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who receives a prophet in the name of a prophet will receive a prophet\u2019s reward. He who receives a righteous man\nin the name of a righteous man will receive a righteous man\u2019s reward.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 10:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever gives one of these little ones just a cup of cold water to drink in the name of a disciple, most certainly I\ntell you he will in no way lose his reward.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 11:1"}, "When Isa had finished directing his twelve disciples, he departed from there to teach and preach in their cities.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 11:2"}, "Now when Yahya heard in the prison the works of Masih, he sent two of his disciples\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 11:3"}, "and said to him, \u201cAre you he who comes, or should we look for another?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 11:4"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo and tell Yahya the things which you hear and see:\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 11:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the blind receive their sight, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf\nhear,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 35:5"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the dead are raised up, and the poor have good news preached to\nthem."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 61:1-4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 11:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed is he who finds no occasion for stumbling in me.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 11:7"}, "As these went their way, Isa began to say to the multitudes concerning Yahya,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 11:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But what did you go out to see? A man in soft clothing? Behold, those who wear soft clothing are in kings\u2019 houses.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 11:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But why did you go out? To see a prophet? Yes, I tell you, and much more than a prophet.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 11:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For this is he, of whom it is written, \u2018Behold, I send my messenger before your face, who will prepare your way\nbefore you.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Malachi 3:1 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 11:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, amongst those who are born of women there has not arisen anyone greater than Yahya the\nBaptiser; yet he who is least in the Kingdom of Heaven is greater than he.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 11:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["From the days of Yahya the Baptiser until now, the Kingdom of Heaven suffers violence, and the violent take it by\nforce."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, plunder it. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 11:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For all the prophets and the law prophesied until Yahya.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 11:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If you are willing to receive it, this is Ilyas, who is to come.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 11:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who has ears to hear, let him hear."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 11:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut to what shall I compare this generation? It is like children sitting in the marketplaces, who call to their\ncompanions "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 11:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and say, \u2018We played the flute for you, and you didn\u2019t dance. We mourned for you, and you didn\u2019t lament.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 11:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Yahya came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, \u2018He has a demon.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 11:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, \u2018Behold, a gluttonous man and a drunkard, a friend of tax\ncollectors and sinners!\u2019 But wisdom is justified by her children.\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cactions\u201d instead of \u201cchildren\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 11:20"}, "Then he began to denounce the cities in which most of his mighty works had been done, because they didn\u2019t repent.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 11:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon which were\ndone in you, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 11:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you, it will be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon on the day of judgement than for you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 11:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You, Capernaum, who are exalted to heaven, you will go down to Hades.\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For if the mighty works had been done in Sodom which were done in you, it would have\nremained until today. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 11:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you that it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom, on the day of judgement, than for\nyou.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 11:25"}, "At that time, Isa answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you hid these things from the wise\nand understanding, and revealed them to infants. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 11:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Yes, Father, for so it was well-pleasing in your sight.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 11:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["All things have been delivered to me by my Father. No one knows the Son, except the Father; neither does anyone know\nthe Father, except the Son, and he to whom the Son desires to reveal\nhim."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 11:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCome to me, all you who labour and are heavily burdened, and I will give you rest.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 11:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me, for I am gentle and humble in heart; and you will find rest for your\nsouls. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 11:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 12:1"}, "At that time, Isa went on the Sabbath day through the grain fields. His disciples were hungry and began to pluck heads of\ngrain and to eat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 12:2"}, "But the Pharisees, when they saw it, said to him, \u201cBehold, your disciples do what is not lawful to do on the Sabbath.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 12:3"}, "But he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHaven\u2019t you read what Dawood did, when he was hungry, and those who were with him;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 12:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["how he entered into Allah\u2019s house, and ate the show bread, which was not lawful for him to eat, neither for those who\nwere with him, but only for the priests?"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["1 Samuel\n21:3-6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 12:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or have you not read in the law, that on the Sabbath day, the priests in the temple profane the Sabbath, and are\nguiltless? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 12:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you that one greater than the temple is here.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 12:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if you had known what this means, \u2018I desire mercy, and not\nsacrifice,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Hosea 6:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["you wouldn\u2019t have condemned the guiltless.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 12:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 12:9"}, "He departed from there, and went into their synagogue. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 12:10"}, "And behold there was a man with a withered hand. They asked him, \u201cIs it lawful to heal on the Sabbath day?\u201d that they\nmight accuse him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 12:11"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat man is there amongst you, who has one sheep, and if this one falls into a pit on the Sabbath\nday, won\u2019t he grab on to it, and lift it out? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 12:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Of how much more value then is a man than a sheep! Therefore it is lawful to do good on the Sabbath\nday.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 12:13"}, "Then he told the man, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cStretch out your hand.\u201d"]}, " He stretched it out; and it was restored whole, just like the\nother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 12:14"}, "But the Pharisees went out, and conspired against him, how they might destroy him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 12:15"}, "Isa, perceiving that, withdrew from there. Great multitudes followed him; and he healed them all,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 12:16"}, "and commanded them that they should not make him known: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 12:17"}, "that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 12:18"}, "\u201cBehold, my servant whom I have chosen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my beloved in whom my soul is well pleased: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will put my Spirit on him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will proclaim justice to the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 12:19"}, "He will not strive, nor shout; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither will anyone hear his voice in the streets. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 12:20"}, "He won\u2019t break a bruised reed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He won\u2019t quench a smoking flax, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["until he leads justice to victory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 12:21"}, "In his name, the nations will hope.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n42:1-4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 12:22"}, "Then one possessed by a demon, blind and mute, was brought to him and he healed him, so that the blind and mute man both\nspoke and saw. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 12:23"}, "All the multitudes were amazed, and said, \u201cCan this be the son of Dawood?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 12:24"}, "But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, \u201cThis man does not cast out demons, except by Beelzebul, the prince of the\ndemons.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 12:25"}, "Knowing their thoughts, Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEvery kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation, and every\ncity or house divided against itself will not stand. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 12:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If Iblis casts out Satan, he is divided against himself. How then will his kingdom stand?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 12:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If I by Beelzebul cast out demons, by whom do your children cast them out? Therefore they will be your judges.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 12:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if I by the Spirit of Allah cast out demons, then Allah\u2019s Kingdom has come upon you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 12:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or how can one enter into the house of the strong man, and plunder his goods, unless he first bind the strong man?\nThen he will plunder his house."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 12:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe who is not with me is against me, and he who doesn\u2019t gather with me, scatters.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 12:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore I tell you, every sin and blasphemy will be forgiven men, but the blasphemy against the Spirit will not be\nforgiven men. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 12:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever speaks a word against the Son of Man, it will be forgiven him; but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit,\nit will not be forgiven him, neither in this age, nor in that which is to\ncome."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 12:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEither make the tree good, and its fruit good, or make the tree corrupt, and its fruit corrupt; for the tree is\nknown by its fruit. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 12:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You offspring of vipers, how can you, being evil, speak good things? For out of the abundance of the heart, the\nmouth speaks. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 12:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The good man out of his good treasure brings out good things, and the evil man out of his evil\ntreasure"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cof the heart\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["brings out evil things.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 12:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I tell you that every idle word that men speak, they will give account of it in the day of judgement.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 12:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For by your words you will be justified, and by your words you will be\ncondemned.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 12:38"}, "Then certain of the scribes and Pharisees answered, \u201cTeacher, we want to see a sign from you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 12:39"}, "But he answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAn evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign, but no sign will be given to it but the\nsign of Yunus the prophet. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 12:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For as Yunus was three days and three nights in the belly of the whale, so will the Son of Man be three days and\nthree nights in the heart of the earth. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 12:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The men of Nineveh will stand up in the judgement with this generation, and will condemn it, for they repented at\nthe preaching of Yunus; and behold, someone greater than Yunus is here.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 12:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The queen of the south will rise up in the judgement with this generation, and will condemn it, for she came from\nthe ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Sulaiman; and behold, someone greater than Sulaiman is here.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 12:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When an unclean spirit has gone out of a man, he passes through waterless places, seeking rest, and doesn\u2019t find it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 12:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then he says, \u2018I will return into my house from which I came out,\u2019 and when he has come back, he finds it empty,\nswept, and put in order. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 12:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then he goes, and takes with himself seven other spirits more evil than he is, and they enter in and dwell there.\nThe last state of that man becomes worse than the first. Even so will it be also to this evil\ngeneration.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 12:46"}, "While he was yet speaking to the multitudes, behold, his mother and his brothers stood outside, seeking to speak to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 12:47"}, "One said to him, \u201cBehold, your mother and your brothers stand outside, seeking to speak to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 12:48"}, "But he answered him who spoke to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho is my mother? Who are my\nbrothers?\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MAT 12:49"}, "He stretched out his hand towards his disciples, and said,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, my mother and my brothers! "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MAT 12:50"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever does the will of my Father who is in heaven, he is my brother, and sister, and\nmother.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 13:1"}, "On that day Isa went out of the house, and sat by the seaside.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 13:2"}, "Great multitudes gathered to him, so that he entered into a boat, and sat, and all the multitude stood on the beach.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 13:3"}, "He spoke to them many things in parables, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, a farmer went out to sow.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 13:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["As he sowed, some seeds fell by the roadside, and the birds came and devoured them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 13:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell on rocky ground, where they didn\u2019t have much soil, and immediately they sprang up, because they had no\ndepth of earth. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 13:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When the sun had risen, they were scorched. Because they had no root, they withered away.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 13:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell amongst thorns. The thorns grew up and choked them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 13:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell on good soil, and yielded fruit: some one hundred times as much, some sixty, and some thirty.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 13:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who has ears to hear, let him hear.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 13:10"}, "The disciples came, and said to him, \u201cWhy do you speak to them in parables?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 13:11"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTo you it is given to know the mysteries of the Kingdom of Heaven, but it is not given to them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 13:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever has, to him will be given, and he will have abundance, but whoever doesn\u2019t have, from him will be taken\naway even that which he has. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 13:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore I speak to them in parables, because seeing they don\u2019t see, and hearing, they don\u2019t hear, neither do they\nunderstand. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 13:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["In them the prophecy of Isaiah is fulfilled, which says,\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018By hearing you will hear,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will in no way understand;"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Seeing you will see,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will in no way perceive:"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 13:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for this people\u2019s heart has grown callous,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["their ears are dull of hearing,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["they have closed their eyes;"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["or else perhaps they might perceive with their eyes,"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["hear with their ears,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["understand with their heart,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and would turn again;"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and I would heal them.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 6:9-10"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 13:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut blessed are your eyes, for they see; and your ears, for they hear.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 13:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For most certainly I tell you that many prophets and righteous men desired to see the things which you see, and\ndidn\u2019t see them; and to hear the things which you hear, and didn\u2019t hear\nthem."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 13:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHear, then, the parable of the farmer. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 13:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When anyone hears the word of the Kingdom, and doesn\u2019t understand it, the evil one comes, and snatches away that\nwhich has been sown in his heart. This is what was sown by the roadside.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 13:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What was sown on the rocky places, this is he who hears the word, and immediately with joy receives it;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 13:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["yet he has no root in himself, but endures for a while. When oppression or persecution arises because of the word,\nimmediately he stumbles. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 13:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What was sown amongst the thorns, this is he who hears the word, but the cares of this age and the deceitfulness of\nriches choke the word, and he becomes unfruitful. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 13:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What was sown on the good ground, this is he who hears the word, and understands it, who most certainly bears fruit,\nand produces, some one hundred times as much, some sixty, and some\nthirty.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 13:24"}, "He set another parable before them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who sowed good seed in his field,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 13:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but while people slept, his enemy came and sowed darnel\nweeds"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["darnel is a weed grass (probably bearded darnel or lolium temulentum) that looks very much like\nwheat until it is mature, when the difference becomes very apparent."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["also amongst the wheat, and went away. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 13:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when the blade sprang up and produced fruit, then the darnel weeds appeared also.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 13:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The servants of the householder came and said to him, \u2018Sir, didn\u2019t you sow good seed in your field? Where did these\ndarnel weeds come from?\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 13:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe said to them, \u2018An enemy has done this.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe servants asked him, \u2018Do you want us to go and gather them up?\u2019\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 13:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut he said, \u2018No, lest perhaps while you gather up the darnel weeds, you root up the wheat with them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 13:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Let both grow together until the harvest, and in the harvest time I will tell the reapers, \u201cFirst, gather up the\ndarnel weeds, and bind them in bundles to burn them; but gather the wheat into my\nbarn.\u201d\u2019\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 13:31"}, "He set another parable before them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Kingdom of Heaven is like a grain of mustard seed, which a man took,\nand sowed in his field; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 13:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["which indeed is smaller than all seeds. But when it is grown, it is greater than the herbs, and becomes a tree, so\nthat the birds of the air come and lodge in its branches.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 13:33"}, "He spoke another parable to them. ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Kingdom of Heaven is like yeast, which a woman took, and hid in three\nmeasures"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, three sata. Three sata is about 39 litres or a bit more than a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["of meal, until it was all leavened.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 13:34"}, "Isa spoke all these things in parables to the multitudes; and without a parable, he didn\u2019t speak to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 13:35"}, "that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI will open my mouth in parables; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will utter things hidden from the foundation of the world.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 78:2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 13:36"}, "Then Isa sent the multitudes away, and went into the house. His disciples came to him, saying, \u201cExplain to us the parable\nof the darnel weeds of the field.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 13:37"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe who sows the good seed is the Son of Man,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 13:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the field is the world; and the good seed, these are the children of the Kingdom; and the darnel weeds are the\nchildren of the evil one. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 13:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The enemy who sowed them is the Iblis. The harvest is the end of the age, and the reapers are angels.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 13:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["As therefore the darnel weeds are gathered up and burnt with fire; so will it be at the end of this age.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 13:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The Son of Man will send out his angels, and they will gather out of his Kingdom all things that cause stumbling,\nand those who do iniquity, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 13:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be the weeping and the gnashing of teeth.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 13:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then the righteous will shine like the sun in the Kingdom of their Father. He who has ears to hear, let him\nhear."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 13:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven is like treasure hidden in the field, which a man found, and hid. In his joy, he goes\nand sells all that he has, and buys that field."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 13:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who is a merchant seeking fine pearls,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 13:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["who having found one pearl of great price, he went and sold all that he had, and bought\nit."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 13:47"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAgain, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a dragnet, that was cast into the sea, and gathered some fish of every kind,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 13:48"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["which, when it was filled, they drew up on the beach. They sat down, and gathered the good into containers, but the\nbad they threw away. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MAT 13:49"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So will it be in the end of the world."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:49\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": [" or, end of the age."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The angels will come and separate the wicked from amongst the righteous,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MAT 13:50"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be the weeping and the gnashing of\nteeth.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MAT 13:51"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHave you understood all these things?\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered him, \u201cYes, Lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MAT 13:52"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTherefore every scribe who has been made a disciple in the Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who is a\nhouseholder, who brings out of his treasure new and old things.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "MAT 13:53"}, "When Isa had finished these parables, he departed from there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "MAT 13:54"}, "Coming into his own country, he taught them in their synagogue, so that they were astonished, and said, \u201cWhere did this\nman get this wisdom, and these mighty works? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "MAT 13:55"}, "Isn\u2019t this the carpenter\u2019s son? Isn\u2019t his mother called Maryam, and his brothers, Yaqub, Joses, Shima\u2019un, and\nYehuda?", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:55 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Judah"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "MAT 13:56"}, "Aren\u2019t all of his sisters with us? Where then did this man get all of these things?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "MAT 13:57"}, "They were offended by him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cA prophet is not without honour, except in his own country, and in his own\nhouse.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "MAT 13:58"}, "He didn\u2019t do many mighty works there because of their unbelief.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 14:1"}, "At that time, Herod the tetrarch heard the report concerning Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 14:2"}, "and said to his servants, \u201cThis is Yahya the Baptiser. He is risen from the dead. That is why these powers work in him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 14:3"}, "For Herod had arrested Yahya, and bound him, and put him in prison for the sake of Herodias, his brother Philip\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 14:4"}, "For Yahya said to him, \u201cIt is not lawful for you to have her.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 14:5"}, "When he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a prophet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 14:6"}, "But when Herod\u2019s birthday came, the daughter of Herodias danced amongst them and pleased Herod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 14:7"}, "Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatever she should ask.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 14:8"}, "She, being prompted by her mother, said, \u201cGive me here on a platter the head of Yahya the Baptiser.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 14:9"}, "The king was grieved, but for the sake of his oaths, and of those who sat at the table with him, he commanded it to be\ngiven, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 14:10"}, "and he sent and beheaded Yahya in the prison. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 14:11"}, "His head was brought on a platter, and given to the young lady; and she brought it to her mother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 14:12"}, "His disciples came, and took the body, and buried it. Then they went and told Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 14:13"}, "Now when Isa heard this, he withdrew from there in a boat, to a deserted place apart. When the multitudes heard it, they\nfollowed him on foot from the cities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 14:14"}, "Isa went out, and he saw a great multitude. He had compassion on them, and healed their sick.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 14:15"}, "When evening had come, his disciples came to him, saying, \u201cThis place is deserted, and the hour is already late. Send the\nmultitudes away, that they may go into the villages, and buy themselves food.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 14:16"}, "But Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThey don\u2019t need to go away. You give them something to\neat.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 14:17"}, "They told him, \u201cWe only have here five loaves and two fish.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 14:18"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBring them here to me.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 14:19"}, "He commanded the multitudes to sit down on the grass; and he took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to\nheaven, he blessed, broke and gave the loaves to the disciples, and the disciples gave to the multitudes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 14:20"}, "They all ate, and were filled. They took up twelve baskets full of that which remained left over from the broken pieces.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 14:21"}, "Those who ate were about five thousand men, in addition to women and children.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 14:22"}, "Immediately Isa made the disciples get into the boat, and to go ahead of him to the other side, while he sent the\nmultitudes away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 14:23"}, "After he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into the mountain by himself to pray. When evening had come, he was\nthere alone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 14:24"}, "But the boat was now in the middle of the sea, distressed by the waves, for the wind was contrary.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 14:25"}, "In the fourth watch of the night,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The night was equally divided into four watches, so the fourth watch\nis approximately 3:00 a.m. to sunrise. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " Isa came to them, walking on the\nsea.", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["14:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["See Ayyub 9:8"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 14:26"}, "When the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were troubled, saying, \u201cIt\u2019s a ghost!\u201d and they cried out for fear.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 14:27"}, "But immediately Isa spoke to them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCheer up! It is I!\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, I AM!"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t be afraid.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 14:28"}, "Peter answered him and said, \u201cLord, if it is you, command me to come to you on the waters.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 14:29"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCome!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Peter stepped down from the boat, and walked on the waters to come to Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 14:30"}, "But when he saw that the wind was strong, he was afraid, and beginning to sink, he cried out, saying, \u201cLord, save me!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 14:31"}, "Immediately Isa stretched out his hand, took hold of him, and said to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou of little faith, why did you doubt?\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 14:32"}, "When they got up into the boat, the wind ceased. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 14:33"}, "Those who were in the boat came and worshipped him, saying, \u201cYou are truly the Son of Allah!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 14:34"}, "When they had crossed over, they came to the land of Gennesaret.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 14:35"}, "When the people of that place recognised him, they sent into all that surrounding region, and brought to him all who were\nsick; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 14:36"}, "and they begged him that they might just touch the fringe", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of his garment. As many as touched it were made whole.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 15:1"}, "Then Pharisees and scribes came to Isa from Jerusalem, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 15:2"}, "\u201cWhy do your disciples disobey the tradition of the elders? For they don\u2019t wash their hands when they eat bread.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 15:3"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you also disobey the commandment of Allah because of your tradition?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 15:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Allah commanded, \u2018Honour your father and your mother,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:12; Deuteronomy 5:16"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and, \u2018He who speaks evil of father or mother, let him be put to\ndeath.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 21:17; Leviticus 20:9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 15:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you say, \u2018Whoever may tell his father or his mother, \u201cWhatever help you might otherwise have gotten from me is a\ngift devoted to Allah,\u201d "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 15:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["he shall not honour his father or mother.\u2019 You have made the commandment of Allah void because of your tradition.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 15:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You hypocrites! Well did Isaiah prophesy of you, saying,"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 15:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018These people draw near to me with their mouth,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and honour me with their lips;"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but their heart is far from me."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 15:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["And in vain do they worship me,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["teaching as doctrine rules made by men.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:9\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 29:13 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 15:10"}, "He summoned the multitude, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHear, and understand.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 15:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["That which enters into the mouth doesn\u2019t defile the man; but that which proceeds out of the mouth, this defiles the\nman.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 15:12"}, "Then the disciples came, and said to him, \u201cDo you know that the Pharisees were offended when they heard this saying?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 15:13"}, "But he answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEvery plant which my heavenly Father didn\u2019t plant will be uprooted.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 15:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Leave them alone. They are blind guides of the blind. If the blind guide the blind, both will fall into a\npit.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 15:15"}, "Peter answered him, \u201cExplain the parable to us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 15:16"}, "So Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDo you also still not understand? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 15:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t you understand that whatever goes into the mouth passes into the belly, and then out of the body?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 15:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But the things which proceed out of the mouth come out of the heart, and they defile the man.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 15:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For out of the heart come evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, sexual sins, thefts, false testimony, and blasphemies.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 15:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["These are the things which defile the man; but to eat with unwashed hands doesn\u2019t defile the\nman.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 15:21"}, "Isa went out from there, and withdrew into the region of Tyre and Sidon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 15:22"}, "Behold, a Canaanite woman came out from those borders, and cried, saying, \u201cHave mercy on me, Lord, you son of Dawood! My\ndaughter is severely possessed by a demon!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 15:23"}, "But he answered her not a word. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["His disciples came and begged him, saying, \u201cSend her away; for she cries after us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 15:24"}, "But he answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI wasn\u2019t sent to anyone but the lost sheep of the house of\nIsrael.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 15:25"}, "But she came and worshipped him, saying, \u201cLord, help me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 15:26"}, "But he answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt is not appropriate to take the children\u2019s bread and throw it to the\ndogs.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 15:27"}, "But she said, \u201cYes, Lord, but even the dogs eat the crumbs which fall from their masters\u2019 table.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 15:28"}, "Then Isa answered her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoman, great is your faith! Be it done to you even as you\ndesire.\u201d"]}, " And her daughter was healed from that hour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 15:29"}, "Isa departed from there, and came near to the sea of Galilee; and he went up into the mountain, and sat there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 15:30"}, "Great multitudes came to him, having with them the lame, blind, mute, maimed, and many others, and they put them down at\nhis feet. He healed them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 15:31"}, "so that the multitude wondered when they saw the mute speaking, the injured healed, the lame walking, and the blind\nseeing\u2014and they glorified Allah of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 15:32"}, "Isa summoned his disciples and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI have compassion on the multitude, because they continue with me now three\ndays and have nothing to eat. I don\u2019t want to send them away fasting, or they might faint on the way.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 15:33"}, "The disciples said to him, \u201cWhere should we get so many loaves in a deserted place as to satisfy so great a multitude?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 15:34"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow many loaves do you have?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cSeven, and a few small fish.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 15:35"}, "He commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 15:36"}, "and he took the seven loaves and the fish. He gave thanks and broke them, and gave to the disciples, and the disciples to\nthe multitudes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 15:37"}, "They all ate, and were filled. They took up seven baskets full of the broken pieces that were left over.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 15:38"}, "Those who ate were four thousand men, in addition to women and children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 15:39"}, "Then he sent away the multitudes, got into the boat, and came into the borders of Magdala.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 16:1"}, "The Pharisees and Sadducees came, and testing him, asked him to show them a sign from heaven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 16:2"}, "But he answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen it is evening, you say, \u2018It will be fair weather, for the sky is red.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 16:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["In the morning, \u2018It will be foul weather today, for the sky is red and threatening.\u2019 Hypocrites! You know how to\ndiscern the appearance of the sky, but you can\u2019t discern the signs of the times!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 16:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign, and there will be no sign given to it, except the sign of the\nprophet Yunus.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He left them, and departed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 16:5"}, "The disciples came to the other side and had forgotten to take bread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 16:6"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake heed and beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and\nSadducees.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 16:7"}, "They reasoned amongst themselves, saying, \u201cWe brought no bread.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 16:8"}, "Isa, perceiving it, said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you reason amongst yourselves, you of little faith, \u2018because you have brought no\nbread?\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 16:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t you yet perceive, neither remember the five loaves for the five thousand, and how many baskets you took up?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 16:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Nor the seven loaves for the four thousand, and how many baskets you took up?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 16:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["How is it that you don\u2019t perceive that I didn\u2019t speak to you concerning bread? But beware of the yeast of the\nPharisees and Sadducees.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 16:12"}, "Then they understood that he didn\u2019t tell them to beware of the yeast of bread, but of the teaching of the Pharisees and\nSadducees. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 16:13"}, "Now when Isa came into the parts of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho do men say that I, the Son of Man, am?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 16:14"}, "They said, \u201cSome say Yahya the Baptiser, some, Ilyas, and others, Jeremiah, or one of the prophets.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 16:15"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut who do you say that I am?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 16:16"}, "Shima\u2019un Peter answered, \u201cYou are the Masih, the Son of the living Allah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 16:17"}, "Isa answered him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBlessed are you, Shima\u2019un Bar Yunus, for flesh and blood has not revealed this to you, but my\nFather who is in heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 16:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I also tell you that you are Peter,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:18\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Peter\u2019s name, Petros in Greek, is the word for a specific rock or\nstone."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and on this rock "]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Greek, petra, a rock mass or\nbedrock."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I will build my assembly, and the gates of Hades"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["will not prevail against it. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 16:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I will give to you the keys of the Kingdom of Heaven, and whatever you bind on earth will have been bound in heaven;\nand whatever you release on earth will have been released in heaven.\u201d"]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 16:20"}, "Then he commanded the disciples that they should tell no one that he was Isa the Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 16:21"}, "From that time, Isa began to show his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem and suffer many things from the elders,\nchief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and the third day be raised up.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 16:22"}, "Peter took him aside, and began to rebuke him, saying, \u201cFar be it from you, Lord! This will never be done to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 16:23"}, "But he turned, and said to Peter, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGet behind me, Shaitan! You are a stumbling block to me, for you are not setting\nyour mind on the things of Allah, but on the things of men.\u201d"]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 16:24"}, "Then Isa said to his disciples, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf anyone desires to come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and\nfollow me. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 16:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever desires to save his life will lose it, and whoever will lose his life for my sake will find it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 16:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For what will it profit a man, if he gains the whole world, and forfeits his life? Or what will a man give in\nexchange for his life? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 16:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Son of Man will come in the glory of his Father with his angels, and then he will render to everyone\naccording to his deeds. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 16:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, there are some standing here who will in no way taste of death, until they see the Son of\nMan coming in his Kingdom.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 17:1"}, "After six days, Isa took with him Peter, Yaqub, and Yahya his brother, and brought them up into a high mountain by\nthemselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 17:2"}, "He was changed", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, transfigured"]}], "caller": "+"}, " before them. His face shone like the sun, and his garments became as\nwhite as the light. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 17:3"}, "Behold, Musa and Ilyas appeared to them talking with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 17:4"}, "Peter answered, and said to Isa, \u201cLord, it is good for us to be here. If you want, let\u2019s make three tents here: one for\nyou, one for Musa, and one for Ilyas.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 17:5"}, "While he was still speaking, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them. Behold, a voice came out of the cloud, saying,\n\u201cThis is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased. Listen to him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 17:6"}, "When the disciples heard it, they fell on their faces, and were very afraid.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 17:7"}, "Isa came and touched them and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGet up, and don\u2019t be afraid.\u201d\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 17:8"}, "Lifting up their eyes, they saw no one, except Isa alone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 17:9"}, "As they were coming down from the mountain, Isa commanded them, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t tell anyone what you saw, until the Son of Man has risen from the\ndead.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 17:10"}, "His disciples asked him, saying, \u201cThen why do the scribes say that Ilyas must come first?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 17:11"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIlyas indeed comes first, and will restore all things,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 17:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but I tell you that Ilyas has come already, and they didn\u2019t recognise him, but did to him whatever they wanted to.\nEven so the Son of Man will also suffer by them.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 17:13"}, "Then the disciples understood that he spoke to them of Yahya the Baptiser.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 17:14"}, "When they came to the multitude, a man came to him, kneeling down to him, and saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 17:15"}, "\u201cLord, have mercy on my son, for he is epileptic, and suffers grievously; for he often falls into the fire, and often\ninto the water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 17:16"}, "So I brought him to your disciples, and they could not cure him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 17:17"}, "Isa answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFaithless and perverse generation! How long will I be with you? How long will I bear with you? Bring\nhim here to me.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 17:18"}, "Isa rebuked him, the demon went out of him, and the boy was cured from that hour.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 17:19"}, "Then the disciples came to Isa privately, and said, \u201cWhy weren\u2019t we able to cast it out?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 17:20"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBecause of your unbelief. For most certainly I tell you, if you have faith as a grain of mustard\nseed, you will tell this mountain, \u2018Move from here to there,\u2019 and it will move; and nothing will be impossible for you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 17:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But this kind doesn\u2019t go out except by prayer and fasting.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 21."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 17:22"}, "While they were staying in Galilee, Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Son of Man is about to be delivered up into the hands of\nmen, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 17:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and they will kill him, and the third day he will be raised up.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They were exceedingly sorry. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 17:24"}, "When they had come to Capernaum, those who collected the didrachma\ncoins", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A didrachma is a Greek silver coin worth 2 drachmas, about as much as 2 Roman denarii, or about 2\ndays\u2019 wages. It was commonly used to pay the half-shekel temple tax, because 2 drachmas were worth one half shekel of silver. A\nshekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " came to Peter, and said, \u201cDoesn\u2019t your teacher pay the didrachma?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 17:25"}, "He said, \u201cYes.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When he came into the house, Isa anticipated him, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you think, Shima\u2019un? From whom do the kings of the\nearth receive toll or tribute? From their children, or from strangers?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 17:26"}, "Peter said to him, \u201cFrom strangers.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTherefore the children are exempt. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 17:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But, lest we cause them to stumble, go to the sea, cast a hook, and take up the first fish that comes up. When you\nhave opened its mouth, you will find a stater coin."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:27\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A stater is a silver coin equivalent to four Attic or two Alexandrian drachmas, or a Jewish shekel: just exactly enough to\ncover the half-shekel temple tax for two people. A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, usually in the form of a\nsilver coin."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Take that, and give it to them for me and you.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 18:1"}, "In that hour the disciples came to Isa, saying, \u201cWho then is greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 18:2"}, "Isa called a little child to himself, and set him in the middle of them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 18:3"}, "and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, unless you turn, and become as little children, you will in no way enter into\nthe Kingdom of Heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 18:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever therefore humbles himself as this little child is the greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 18:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever receives one such little child in my name receives me,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 18:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but whoever causes one of these little ones who believe in me to stumble, it would be better for him if a huge\nmillstone were hung around his neck, and that he were sunk in the depths of the sea.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 18:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to the world because of occasions of stumbling! For it must be that the occasions come, but woe to that person\nthrough whom the occasion comes! "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 18:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your hand or your foot causes you to stumble, cut it off, and cast it from you. It is better for you to enter into\nlife maimed or crippled, rather than having two hands or two feet to be cast into the eternal fire.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 18:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your eye causes you to stumble, pluck it out, and cast it from you. It is better for you to enter into life with\none eye, rather than having two eyes to be cast into the Gehenna"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["of fire. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 18:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["See that you don\u2019t despise one of these little ones, for I tell you that in heaven their angels always see the face\nof my Father who is in heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 18:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Son of Man came to save that which was lost."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 11."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 18:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you think? If a man has one hundred sheep, and one of them goes astray, doesn\u2019t he leave the ninety-nine,\ngo to the mountains, and seek that which has gone astray? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 18:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If he finds it, most certainly I tell you, he rejoices over it more than over the ninety-nine which have not gone\nastray. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 18:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Even so it is not the will of your Father who is in heaven that one of these little ones should\nperish."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 18:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf your brother sins against you, go, show him his fault between you and him alone. If he listens to you, you have\ngained back your brother. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 18:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if he doesn\u2019t listen, take one or two more with you, that at the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may\nbe established."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["18:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 19:15"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 18:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If he refuses to listen to them, tell it to the assembly. If he refuses to hear the assembly also, let him be to you\nas a Gentile or a tax collector. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 18:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, whatever things you bind on earth will have been bound in heaven, and whatever things you\nrelease on earth will have been released in heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 18:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again, assuredly I tell you, that if two of you will agree on earth concerning anything that they will ask, it will\nbe done for them by my Father who is in heaven. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 18:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there I am in the middle of\nthem.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 18:21"}, "Then Peter came and said to him, \u201cLord, how often shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? Until seven times?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 18:22"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI don\u2019t tell you until seven times, but, until seventy times seven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 18:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore the Kingdom of Heaven is like a certain king, who wanted to reconcile accounts with his servants.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 18:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When he had begun to reconcile, one was brought to him who owed him ten thousand\ntalents."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Ten thousand talents (about 300 metric tonnes of silver) represents an extremely large sum of\nmoney, equivalent to about 60,000,000 denarii, where one denarius was typical of one day\u2019s wages for agricultural\nlabour."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 18:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But because he couldn\u2019t pay, his lord commanded him to be sold, with his wife, his children, and all that he had,\nand payment to be made. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 18:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The servant therefore fell down and knelt before him, saying, \u2018Lord, have patience with me, and I will repay you\nall!\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 18:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The lord of that servant, being moved with compassion, released him, and forgave him the\ndebt."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 18:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut that servant went out, and found one of his fellow servants, who owed him one hundred\ndenarii,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["100 denarii was about one sixtieth of a talent, or about 500 grams (1.1 pounds) of\nsilver."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and he grabbed him, and took him by the throat, saying, \u2018Pay me what you\nowe!\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 18:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSo his fellow servant fell down at his feet and begged him, saying, \u2018Have patience with me, and I will repay you!\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 18:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He would not, but went and cast him into prison, until he should pay back that which was due.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 18:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So when his fellow servants saw what was done, they were exceedingly sorry, and came and told their lord all that\nwas done. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 18:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then his lord called him in, and said to him, \u2018You wicked servant! I forgave you all that debt, because you begged\nme. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 18:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Shouldn\u2019t you also have had mercy on your fellow servant, even as I had mercy on you?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 18:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["His lord was angry, and delivered him to the tormentors, until he should pay all that was due to him.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 18:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So my heavenly Father will also do to you, if you don\u2019t each forgive your brother from your hearts for his\nmisdeeds.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 19:1"}, "When Isa had finished these words, he departed from Galilee, and came into the borders of Judea beyond the Jordan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 19:2"}, "Great multitudes followed him, and he healed them there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 19:3"}, "Pharisees came to him, testing him, and saying, \u201cIs it lawful for a man to divorce his wife for any reason?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 19:4"}, "He answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHaven\u2019t you read that he who made them from the beginning made them male and\nfemale,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["19:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 1:27"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 19:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and said, \u2018For this cause a man shall leave his father and mother, and shall be joined to his wife; and the two shall\nbecome one flesh?\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["19:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 2:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 19:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So that they are no more two, but one flesh. What therefore Allah has joined together, don\u2019t let man tear\napart.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 19:7"}, "They asked him, \u201cWhy then did Musa command us to give her a certificate of divorce, and divorce her?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 19:8"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMusa, because of the hardness of your hearts, allowed you to divorce your wives, but from the\nbeginning it has not been so. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 19:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I tell you that whoever divorces his wife, except for sexual immorality, and marries another, commits adultery; and\nhe who marries her when she is divorced commits adultery.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 19:10"}, "His disciples said to him, \u201cIf this is the case of the man with his wife, it is not expedient to marry.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 19:11"}, "But he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNot all men can receive this saying, but those to whom it is given.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 19:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For there are eunuchs who were born that way from their mother\u2019s womb, and there are eunuchs who were made eunuchs\nby men; and there are eunuchs who made themselves eunuchs for the Kingdom of Heaven\u2019s sake. He who is able to receive it, let\nhim receive it.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 19:13"}, "Then little children were brought to him, that he should lay his hands on them and pray; and the disciples rebuked them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 19:14"}, "But Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAllow the little children, and don\u2019t forbid them to come to me; for the Kingdom of Heaven belongs to\nones like these.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 19:15"}, "He laid his hands on them, and departed from there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 19:16"}, "Behold, one came to him and said, \u201cGood teacher, what good thing shall I do, that I may have eternal life?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 19:17"}, "He said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you call me good?"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:17\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["So MT and TR. NU reads \u201cWhy do you ask me about what is good?\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["No one is good but one, that is, Allah. But if you want to enter into life, keep the commandments.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 19:18"}, "He said to him, \u201cWhich ones?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201c\u2018You shall not murder.\u2019 \u2018You shall not commit adultery.\u2019 \u2018You shall not steal.\u2019 \u2018You shall not offer false\ntestimony.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 19:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Honour your father and your mother.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["19:19\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:12-16; Deuteronomy 5:16-20"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["And, \u2018You shall love your neighbour as\nyourself.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["19:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 19:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 19:20"}, "The young man said to him, \u201cAll these things I have observed from my youth. What do I still lack?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 19:21"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf you want to be perfect, go, sell what you have, and give to the poor, and you will have treasure\nin heaven; and come, follow me.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 19:22"}, "But when the young man heard the saying, he went away sad, for he was one who had great possessions.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 19:23"}, "Isa said to his disciples, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I say to you, a rich man will enter into the Kingdom of Heaven with\ndifficulty. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 19:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again I tell you, it is easier for a camel to go through a needle\u2019s eye, than for a rich man to enter into Allah\u2019s\nKingdom.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 19:25"}, "When the disciples heard it, they were exceedingly astonished, saying, \u201cWho then can be saved?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 19:26"}, "Looking at them, Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWith men this is impossible, but with Allah all things are\npossible.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 19:27"}, "Then Peter answered, \u201cBehold, we have left everything, and followed you. What then will we have?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 19:28"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you that you who have followed me, in the regeneration when the Son of Man\nwill sit on the throne of his glory, you also will sit on twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 19:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Everyone who has left houses, or brothers, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my\nname\u2019s sake, will receive one hundred times, and will inherit eternal life.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 19:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But many will be last who are first; and first who are last.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 20:1"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor the Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who was the master of a household, who went out early in the morning to hire\nlabourers for his vineyard. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 20:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When he had agreed with the labourers for a denarius"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A denarius is a silver Roman coin worth 1/25th of a Roman aureus. This was a common wage for a day of farm\nlabour."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["a day, he sent them into his vineyard. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 20:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He went out about the third hour,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Time was measured from sunrise to sunset, so the third hour\nwould be about 9:00 a.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and saw others standing idle in the marketplace.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 20:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He said to them, \u2018You also go into the vineyard, and whatever is right I will give you.\u2019 So they went their way.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 20:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again he went out about the sixth and the ninth hour,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["noon and 3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and did likewise. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 20:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["About the eleventh hour"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["5:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["he went out, and found others standing idle. He said to them, \u2018Why do you stand here all day idle?\u2019\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 20:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThey said to him, \u2018Because no one has hired us.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe said to them, \u2018You also go into the vineyard, and you will receive whatever is right.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 20:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When evening had come, the lord of the vineyard said to his manager, \u2018Call the labourers and pay them their wages,\nbeginning from the last to the first.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 20:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen those who were hired at about the eleventh hour came, they each received a denarius.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 20:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When the first came, they supposed that they would receive more; and they likewise each received a denarius.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 20:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When they received it, they murmured against the master of the household,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 20:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["saying, \u2018These last have spent one hour, and you have made them equal to us, who have borne the burden of the day\nand the scorching heat!\u2019 "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 20:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut he answered one of them, \u2018Friend, I am doing you no wrong. Didn\u2019t you agree with me for a denarius?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 20:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Take that which is yours, and go your way. It is my desire to give to this last just as much as to you.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 20:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Isn\u2019t it lawful for me to do what I want to with what I own? Or is your eye evil, because I am good?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 20:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So the last will be first, and the first last. For many are called, but few are\nchosen.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 20:17"}, "As Isa was going up to Jerusalem, he took the twelve disciples aside, and on the way he said to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 20:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and the Son of Man will be delivered to the chief priests and scribes, and\nthey will condemn him to death, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 20:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will hand him over to the Gentiles to mock, to scourge, and to crucify; and the third day he will be raised\nup.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 20:20"}, "Then the mother of the sons of Zebedee came to him with her sons, kneeling and asking a certain thing of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 20:21"}, "He said to her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you want?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said to him, \u201cCommand that these, my two sons, may sit, one on your right hand, and one on your left hand, in your\nKingdom.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 20:22"}, "But Isa answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou don\u2019t know what you are asking. Are you able to drink the cup that I am about to drink, and be\nbaptised with the baptism that I am baptised with?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cWe are able.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 20:23"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou will indeed drink my cup, and be baptised with the baptism that I am baptised with, but to sit\non my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but it is for whom it has been prepared by my\nFather.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 20:24"}, "When the ten heard it, they were indignant with the two brothers.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 20:25"}, "But Isa summoned them, and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou know that the rulers of the nations lord it over them, and their great ones\nexercise authority over them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 20:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It shall not be so amongst you, but whoever desires to become great amongst you shall\nbe"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201clet him be\u201d instead of \u201cshall be\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["your servant. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 20:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever desires to be first amongst you shall be your bondservant,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 20:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["even as the Son of Man came not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for\nmany.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 20:29"}, "As they went out from Jericho, a great multitude followed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 20:30"}, "Behold, two blind men sitting by the road, when they heard that Isa was passing by, cried out, \u201cLord, have mercy on us,\nyou son of Dawood!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 20:31"}, "The multitude rebuked them, telling them that they should be quiet, but they cried out even more, \u201cLord, have mercy on\nus, you son of Dawood!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 20:32"}, "Isa stood still, and called them, and asked, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you want me to do for\nyou?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 20:33"}, "They told him, \u201cLord, that our eyes may be opened.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 20:34"}, "Isa, being moved with compassion, touched their eyes; and immediately their eyes received their sight, and they followed\nhim. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 21:1"}, "When they came near to Jerusalem, and came to Bethsphage,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR & NU read \u201cBethphage\u201d instead of \u201cBethsphage\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to the Mount of Olives, then Isa sent two disciples,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 21:2"}, "saying to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo into the village that is opposite you, and immediately you will find a donkey tied, and a colt\nwith her. Untie them, and bring them to me. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 21:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If anyone says anything to you, you shall say, \u2018The Lord needs them,\u2019 and immediately he will send\nthem.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 21:4"}, "All this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through the prophet, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 21:5"}, "\u201cTell the daughter of Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["behold, your King comes to you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["humble, and riding on a donkey, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["on a colt, the foal of a donkey.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zakariya\n9:9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 21:6"}, "The disciples went, and did just as Isa commanded them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 21:7"}, "and brought the donkey and the colt, and laid their clothes on them; and he sat on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 21:8"}, "A very great multitude spread their clothes on the road. Others cut branches from the trees, and spread them on the road.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 21:9"}, "The multitudes who went in front of him, and those who followed, kept shouting, \u201cHosanna\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cHosanna\u201d means \u201csave us\u201d or \u201chelp us, we pray\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " to the son of Dawood! Blessed is he who comes in the\nname of the Lord! Hosanna in the highest!\u201d ", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur\n118:26"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 21:10"}, "When he had come into Jerusalem, all the city was stirred up, saying, \u201cWho is this?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 21:11"}, "The multitudes said, \u201cThis is the prophet, Isa, from Nazareth of Galilee.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 21:12"}, "Isa entered into the temple of Allah, and drove out all of those who sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the\nmoney changers\u2019 tables and the seats of those who sold the doves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 21:13"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt is written, \u2018My house shall be called a house of\nprayer,\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 56:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but you have made it a den of\nrobbers!\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Jeremiah 7:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 21:14"}, "The blind and the lame came to him in the temple, and he healed them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 21:15"}, "But when the chief priests and the scribes saw the wonderful things that he did, and the children who were crying in the\ntemple and saying, \u201cHosanna to the son of Dawood!\u201d they were indignant,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 21:16"}, "and said to him, \u201cDo you hear what these are saying?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYes. Did you never read, \u2018Out of the mouth of babes and nursing babies you have perfected\npraise?\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 8:2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 21:17"}, "He left them, and went out of the city to Bethany, and camped there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 21:18"}, "Now in the morning, as he returned to the city, he was hungry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 21:19"}, "Seeing a fig tree by the road, he came to it, and found nothing on it but leaves. He said to it,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cLet there be no fruit from you forever!\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Immediately the fig tree withered away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 21:20"}, "When the disciples saw it, they marvelled, saying, \u201cHow did the fig tree immediately wither away?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 21:21"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, if you have faith, and don\u2019t doubt, you will not only do what was done\nto the fig tree, but even if you told this mountain, \u2018Be taken up and cast into the sea,\u2019 it would be done.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 21:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["All things, whatever you ask in prayer, believing, you will\nreceive.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 21:23"}, "When he had come into the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came to him as he was teaching, and\nsaid, \u201cBy what authority do you do these things? Who gave you this authority?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 21:24"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI also will ask you one question, which if you tell me, I likewise will tell you by what\nauthority I do these things. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 21:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The baptism of Yahya, where was it from? From heaven or from men?\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They reasoned with themselves, saying, \u201cIf we say, \u2018From heaven,\u2019 he will ask us, \u2018Why then did you not believe him?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 21:26"}, "But if we say, \u2018From men,\u2019 we fear the multitude, for all hold Yahya as a prophet.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 21:27"}, "They answered Isa, and said, \u201cWe don\u2019t know.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He also said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNeither will I tell you by what authority I do these things.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 21:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But what do you think? A man had two sons, and he came to the first, and said, \u2018Son, go work today in my vineyard.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 21:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He answered, \u2018I will not,\u2019 but afterward he changed his mind, and went.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 21:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He came to the second, and said the same thing. He answered, \u2018I\u2019m going, sir,\u2019 but he didn\u2019t go.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 21:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Which of the two did the will of his father?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cThe first.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you that the tax collectors and the prostitutes are entering into Allah\u2019s\nKingdom before you. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 21:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Yahya came to you in the way of righteousness, and you didn\u2019t believe him, but the tax collectors and the\nprostitutes believed him. When you saw it, you didn\u2019t even repent afterward, that you might believe him.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 21:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHear another parable. There was a man who was a master of a household, who planted a vineyard, set a hedge about\nit, dug a wine press in it, built a tower, leased it out to farmers, and went into another country.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 21:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When the season for the fruit came near, he sent his servants to the farmers, to receive his fruit.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 21:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The farmers took his servants, beat one, killed another, and stoned another.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 21:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again, he sent other servants more than the first: and they treated them the same way.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 21:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But afterward he sent to them his son, saying, \u2018They will respect my son.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 21:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But the farmers, when they saw the son, said amongst themselves, \u2018This is the heir. Come, let\u2019s kill him, and seize\nhis inheritance.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 21:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["So they took him, and threw him out of the vineyard, and killed him.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 21:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When therefore the lord of the vineyard comes, what will he do to those\nfarmers?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 21:41"}, "They told him, \u201cHe will miserably destroy those miserable men, and will lease out the vineyard to other farmers, who will\ngive him the fruit in its season.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 21:42"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDid you never read in the Scriptures,\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018The stone which the builders rejected"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["was made the head of the corner."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["This was from the Lord."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It is marvellous in our eyes?\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["21:42 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur\n118:22-23"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 21:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTherefore I tell you, Allah\u2019s Kingdom will be taken away from you, and will be given to a nation producing its\nfruit. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 21:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who falls on this stone will be broken to pieces, but on whomever it will fall, it will scatter him as\ndust.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 21:45"}, "When the chief priests and the Pharisees heard his parables, they perceived that he spoke about them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 21:46"}, "When they sought to seize him, they feared the multitudes, because they considered him to be a prophet.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 22:1"}, "Isa answered and spoke to them again in parables, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 22:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Kingdom of Heaven is like a certain king, who made a wedding feast for his son,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 22:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and sent out his servants to call those who were invited to the wedding feast, but they would not come.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 22:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again he sent out other servants, saying, \u2018Tell those who are invited, \u201cBehold, I have prepared my dinner. My cattle\nand my fatlings are killed, and all things are ready. Come to the wedding feast!\u201d\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 22:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his own farm, another to his merchandise,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 22:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and the rest grabbed his servants, and treated them shamefully, and killed them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 22:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When the king heard that, he was angry, and sent his armies, destroyed those murderers, and burnt their\ncity."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 22:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen he said to his servants, \u2018The wedding is ready, but those who were invited weren\u2019t worthy.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 22:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Go therefore to the intersections of the highways, and as many as you may find, invite to the wedding feast.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 22:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Those servants went out into the highways, and gathered together as many as they found, both bad and good. The\nwedding was filled with guests. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 22:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man who didn\u2019t have on wedding clothing,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 22:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and he said to him, \u2018Friend, how did you come in here not wearing wedding clothing?\u2019 He was speechless.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 22:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then the king said to the servants, \u2018Bind him hand and foot, take him away, and throw him into the outer darkness.\nThat is where the weeping and grinding of teeth will be.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 22:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For many are called, but few chosen.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 22:15"}, "Then the Pharisees went and took counsel how they might entrap him in his talk.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 22:16"}, "They sent their disciples to him, along with the Herodians, saying, \u201cTeacher, we know that you are honest, and teach the\nway of Allah in truth, no matter whom you teach, for you aren\u2019t partial to anyone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 22:17"}, "Tell us therefore, what do you think? Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 22:18"}, "But Isa perceived their wickedness, and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you test me, you hypocrites?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 22:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Show me the tax money.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They brought to him a denarius. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 22:20"}, "He asked them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhose is this image and inscription?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 22:21"}, "They said to him, \u201cCaesar\u2019s.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGive therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar\u2019s, and to Allah the things that are\nAllah\u2019s.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 22:22"}, "When they heard it, they marvelled, and left him, and went away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 22:23"}, "On that day Sadducees (those who say that there is no resurrection) came to him. They asked him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 22:24"}, "saying, \u201cTeacher, Musa said, \u2018If a man dies, having no children, his brother shall marry his wife, and raise up\noffspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " for his brother.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 22:25"}, "Now there were with us seven brothers. The first married and died, and having no offspring left his wife to his brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 22:26"}, "In the same way, the second also, and the third, to the seventh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 22:27"}, "After them all, the woman died. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 22:28"}, "In the resurrection therefore, whose wife will she be of the seven? For they all had her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 22:29"}, "But Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou are mistaken, not knowing the Scriptures, nor the power of Allah.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 22:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For in the resurrection they neither marry, nor are given in marriage, but are like Allah\u2019s angels in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 22:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But concerning the resurrection of the dead, haven\u2019t you read that which was spoken to you by Allah, saying,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 22:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018I am Allah of Ibrahim, and Allah of Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Allah of\nYaqub?\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["22:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 3:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Allah is not Allah of the dead, but of the\nliving.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 22:33"}, "When the multitudes heard it, they were astonished at his teaching.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 22:34"}, "But the Pharisees, when they heard that he had silenced the Sadducees, gathered themselves together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 22:35"}, "One of them, a lawyer, asked him a question, testing him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 22:36"}, "\u201cTeacher, which is the greatest commandment in the law?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 22:37"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201c\u2018You shall love Allah your Lord with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your\nmind.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["22:37 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 6:5 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 22:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["This is the first and great commandment. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 22:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["A second likewise is this, \u2018You shall love your neighbour as\nyourself.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["22:39 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 19:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 22:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The whole law and the prophets depend on these two commandments.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 22:41"}, "Now while the Pharisees were gathered together, Isa asked them a question,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 22:42"}, "saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you think of the Masih? Whose son is he?\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cOf Dawood.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 22:43"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow then does Dawood in the Spirit call him Lord,\nsaying,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 22:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018The Lord said to my Lord,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["sit on my right hand,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet?\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["22:44 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 110:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 22:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf then Dawood calls him Lord, how is he his son?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 22:46"}, "No one was able to answer him a word, neither did any man dare ask him any more questions from that day forward.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 23:1"}, "Then Isa spoke to the multitudes and to his disciples, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 23:2"}, "saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe scribes and the Pharisees sat on Musa\u2019s seat.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 23:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["All things therefore whatever they tell you to observe, observe and do, but don\u2019t do their works; for they say, and\ndon\u2019t do. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 23:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For they bind heavy burdens that are grievous to be borne, and lay them on men\u2019s shoulders; but they themselves will\nnot lift a finger to help them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 23:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But they do all their works to be seen by men. They make their phylacteries\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["phylacteries (tefillin in Hebrew) are small leather pouches that some Jewish men wear on their forehead\nand arm in prayer. They are used to carry a small scroll with some Scripture in it. See\nDeuteronomy 6:8."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["broad, enlarge the fringes"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:5\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassels"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["of their garments, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 23:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and love the place of honour at feasts, the best seats in the synagogues,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 23:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the salutations in the marketplaces, and to be called \u2018Rabbi, Rabbi\u2019 by men.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 23:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But don\u2019t you be called \u2018Rabbi,\u2019 for one is your teacher, the Masih, and all of you are brothers.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 23:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Call no man on the earth your father, for one is your Father, he who is in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 23:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Neither be called masters, for one is your master, the Masih.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 23:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But he who is greatest amongst you will be your servant.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 23:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be\nexalted."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 23:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you devour widows\u2019 houses, and as a pretence you make long\nprayers. Therefore you will receive greater condemnation."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 23:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! Because you shut up the Kingdom of Heaven against men; for you\ndon\u2019t enter in yourselves, neither do you allow those who are entering in to\nenter."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Some Greek texts reverse the order of verses 13 and 14, and some omit verse 13, numbering verse\n14 as 13. NU omits verse 14."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 23:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you travel around by sea and land to make one proselyte; and when\nhe becomes one, you make him twice as much a son of Gehenna"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["as yourselves. "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 23:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, you blind guides, who say, \u2018Whoever swears by the temple, it is nothing; but whoever swears by the gold\nof the temple, he is obligated.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 23:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You blind fools! For which is greater, the gold, or the temple that sanctifies the gold?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 23:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Whoever swears by the altar, it is nothing; but whoever swears by the gift that is on it, he is obligated?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 23:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You blind fools! For which is greater, the gift, or the altar that sanctifies the gift?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 23:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He therefore who swears by the altar, swears by it, and by everything on it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 23:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who swears by the temple, swears by it, and by him who has been\nliving"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201clives\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["in it. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 23:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who swears by heaven, swears by the throne of Allah, and by him who sits on\nit."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 23:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you tithe mint, dill, and\ncumin,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["cumin is an aromatic seed from Cuminum cyminum, resembling caraway in flavour and appearance. It\nis used as a spice."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and have left undone the weightier matters of the law: justice, mercy, and faith. But you ought to\nhave done these, and not to have left the other undone. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 23:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You blind guides, who strain out a gnat, and swallow a camel!\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 23:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you clean the outside of the cup and of the platter, but within\nthey are full of extortion and unrighteousness."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:25\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cself-indulgence\u201d instead of \u201cunrighteousness\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 23:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You blind Pharisee, first clean the inside of the cup and of the platter, that its outside may become clean\nalso."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 23:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you are like whitened tombs, which outwardly appear beautiful,\nbut inwardly are full of dead men\u2019s bones, and of all uncleanness.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 23:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Even so you also outwardly appear righteous to men, but inwardly you are full of hypocrisy and\niniquity."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 23:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWoe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you build the tombs of the prophets, and decorate the tombs of\nthe righteous, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 23:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and say, \u2018If we had lived in the days of our fathers, we wouldn\u2019t have been partakers with them in the blood of the\nprophets.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 23:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore you testify to yourselves that you are children of those who killed the prophets.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 23:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Fill up, then, the measure of your fathers. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 23:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You serpents, you offspring of vipers, how will you escape the judgement of\nGehenna?"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 23:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore behold, I send to you prophets, wise men, and scribes. Some of them you will kill and crucify; and some of\nthem you will scourge in your synagogues, and persecute from city to city;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 23:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["that on you may come all the righteous blood shed on the earth, from the blood of righteous Habil to the blood of\nZachariah son of Barachiah, whom you killed between the sanctuary and the altar.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 23:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, all these things will come upon this\ngeneration."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 23:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cJerusalem, Jerusalem, who kills the prophets, and stones those who are sent to her! How often I would have gathered\nyour children together, even as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings, and you would not!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 23:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Behold, your house is left to you desolate. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 23:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For I tell you, you will not see me from now on, until you say, \u2018Blessed is he who comes in the name of the\nLord!\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["23:39 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 118:26 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 24:1"}, "Isa went out from the temple, and was going on his way. His disciples came to him to show him the buildings of the\ntemple. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 24:2"}, "But he answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou see all of these things, don\u2019t you? Most certainly I tell you, there will not be left here\none stone on another, that will not be thrown down.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 24:3"}, "As he sat on the Mount of Olives, the disciples came to him privately, saying, \u201cTell us, when will these things be? What\nis the sign of your coming, and of the end of the age?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 24:4"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBe careful that no one leads you astray.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 24:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For many will come in my name, saying, \u2018I am the Masih,\u2019 and will lead many astray.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 24:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You will hear of wars and rumours of wars. See that you aren\u2019t troubled, for all this must happen, but the end is not\nyet. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 24:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom; and there will be famines, plagues, and earthquakes\nin various places. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 24:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But all these things are the beginning of birth pains.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 24:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then they will deliver you up to oppression, and will kill you. You will be hated by all of the nations for my name\u2019s\nsake. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 24:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then many will stumble, and will deliver up one another, and will hate one another.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 24:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Many false prophets will arise, and will lead many astray.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 24:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Because iniquity will be multiplied, the love of many will grow cold.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 24:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But he who endures to the end will be saved. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 24:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["This Good News of the Kingdom will be preached in the whole world for a testimony to all the nations, and then the\nend will come."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 24:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen, therefore, you see the abomination of desolation,"]}, "\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["24:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Daniel 9:27; 11:31; 12:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["which was spoken of through Daniel the prophet, standing in the holy place\n(let the reader understand), "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 24:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 24:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Let him who is on the housetop not go down to take out the things that are in his house.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 24:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Let him who is in the field not return back to get his clothes.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 24:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But woe to those who are with child and to nursing mothers in those days!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 24:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Pray that your flight will not be in the winter, nor on a Sabbath,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 24:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for then there will be great suffering,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:21\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, oppression"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["such as has not been from the beginning of the world until now, no, nor ever will be.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 24:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Unless those days had been shortened, no flesh would have been saved. But for the sake of the chosen ones, those\ndays will be shortened. "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 24:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen if any man tells you, \u2018Behold, here is the Masih,\u2019 or, \u2018There,\u2019 don\u2019t believe it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 24:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For there will arise false christs, and false prophets, and they will show great signs and wonders, so as to lead\nastray, if possible, even the chosen ones."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 24:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, I have told you beforehand. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 24:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If therefore they tell you, \u2018Behold, he is in the wilderness,\u2019 don\u2019t go out; or \u2018Behold, he is in the inner rooms,\u2019\ndon\u2019t believe it. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 24:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For as the lightning flashes from the east, and is seen even to the west, so will the coming of the Son of Man be.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 24:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For wherever the carcass is, that is where the vultures"]}, "\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, eagles"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["gather together. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 24:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But immediately after the suffering"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:29\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, oppression"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["of those days, the sun will be darkened, the moon will not give its light, the stars will fall from\nthe sky, and the powers of the heavens will be shaken;"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["24:29\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 13:10; 34:4 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 24:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and then the sign of the Son of Man will appear in the sky. Then all the tribes of the earth will mourn, and they\nwill see the Son of Man coming on the clouds of the sky with power and great glory.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 24:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He will send out his angels with a great sound of a trumpet, and they will gather together his chosen ones from the\nfour winds, from one end of the sky to the other."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 24:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNow from the fig tree learn this parable. When its branch has now become tender, and produces its leaves, you know\nthat the summer is near. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 24:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Even so you also, when you see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 24:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, this generation"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:34\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cgeneration\u201d (genea) can also be translated as \u201crace.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["will not pass away, until all these things are accomplished.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 24:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 24:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But no one knows of that day and hour, not even the angels of\nheaven,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU adds \u201cnor the son\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but my Father\nonly."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 24:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAs the days of Nuh were, so will the coming of the Son of Man be.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 24:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For as in those days which were before the flood they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage,\nuntil the day that Nuh entered into the ship, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 24:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and they didn\u2019t know until the flood came, and took them all away, so will the coming of the Son of Man be.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 24:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then two men will be in the field: one will be taken and one will be left.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 24:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Two women will be grinding at the mill: one will be taken and one will be left.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 24:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch therefore, for you don\u2019t know in what hour your Lord comes.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 24:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But know this, that if the master of the house had known in what watch of the night the thief was coming, he would\nhave watched, and would not have allowed his house to be broken into.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 24:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore also be ready, for in an hour that you don\u2019t expect, the Son of Man will\ncome."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 24:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho then is the faithful and wise servant, whom his lord has set over his household, to give them their food in due\nseason? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 24:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Blessed is that servant whom his lord finds doing so when he comes.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 24:47"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you that he will set him over all that he has.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 24:48"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if that evil servant should say in his heart, \u2018My lord is delaying his coming,\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MAT 24:49"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and begins to beat his fellow servants, and eat and drink with the drunkards,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MAT 24:50"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the lord of that servant will come in a day when he doesn\u2019t expect it, and in an hour when he doesn\u2019t know it,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MAT 24:51"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will cut him in pieces, and appoint his portion with the hypocrites. That is where the weeping and grinding of\nteeth will be. "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 25:1"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen the Kingdom of Heaven will be like ten virgins, who took their lamps, and went out to meet the bridegroom.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 25:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Five of them were foolish, and five were wise. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 25:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Those who were foolish, when they took their lamps, took no oil with them,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 25:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but the wise took oil in their vessels with their lamps.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 25:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Now while the bridegroom delayed, they all slumbered and slept.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 25:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But at midnight there was a cry, \u2018Behold! The bridegroom is coming! Come out to meet him!\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 25:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then all those virgins arose, and trimmed their lamps."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The end of the wick of an oil lamp needs to be cut off periodically to avoid having it become clogged with carbon\ndeposits. The wick height is also adjusted so that the flame burns evenly and gives good light without producing a lot of\nsmoke."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 25:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The foolish said to the wise, \u2018Give us some of your oil, for our lamps are going out.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 25:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But the wise answered, saying, \u2018What if there isn\u2019t enough for us and you? You go rather to those who sell, and buy\nfor yourselves.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 25:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["While they went away to buy, the bridegroom came, and those who were ready went in with him to the wedding feast,\nand the door was shut. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 25:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Afterward the other virgins also came, saying, \u2018Lord, Lord, open to us.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 25:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But he answered, \u2018Most certainly I tell you, I don\u2019t know you.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 25:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch therefore, for you don\u2019t know the day nor the hour in which the Son of Man is\ncoming."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 25:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor it is like a man, going into another country, who called his own servants, and entrusted his goods to them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 25:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["To one he gave five talents,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds (usually used to\nweigh silver unless otherwise specified)"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["to another two, to another one; to each according to his own ability. Then he\nwent on his journey. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 25:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Immediately he who received the five talents went and traded with them, and made another five talents.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 25:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["In the same way, he also who got the two gained another two.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 25:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But he who received the one talent went away and dug in the earth, and hid his lord\u2019s\nmoney."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 25:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNow after a long time the lord of those servants came, and reconciled accounts with them.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 25:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who received the five talents came and brought another five talents, saying, \u2018Lord, you delivered to me five\ntalents. Behold, I have gained another five talents in addition to\nthem.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 25:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHis lord said to him, \u2018Well done, good and faithful servant. You have been faithful over a few things, I will set\nyou over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 25:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe also who got the two talents came and said, \u2018Lord, you delivered to me two talents. Behold, I have gained\nanother two talents in addition to them.\u2019 "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 25:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHis lord said to him, \u2018Well done, good and faithful servant. You have been faithful over a few things, I will set\nyou over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 25:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe also who had received the one talent came and said, \u2018Lord, I knew you that you are a hard man, reaping where you\ndidn\u2019t sow, and gathering where you didn\u2019t scatter. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 25:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I was afraid, and went away and hid your talent in the earth. Behold, you have what is\nyours.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 25:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut his lord answered him, \u2018You wicked and slothful servant. You knew that I reap where I didn\u2019t sow, and gather\nwhere I didn\u2019t scatter. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 25:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You ought therefore to have deposited my money with the bankers, and at my coming I should have received back my own\nwith interest. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 25:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Take away therefore the talent from him, and give it to him who has the ten talents.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 25:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For to everyone who has will be given, and he will have abundance, but from him who doesn\u2019t have, even that which he\nhas will be taken away. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 25:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Throw out the unprofitable servant into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of\nteeth.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 25:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut when the Son of Man comes in his glory, and all the holy angels with him, then he will sit on the throne of his\nglory. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 25:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Before him all the nations will be gathered, and he will separate them one from another, as a shepherd separates the\nsheep from the goats. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 25:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He will set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 25:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then the King will tell those on his right hand, \u2018Come, blessed of my Father, inherit the Kingdom prepared for you\nfrom the foundation of the world; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 25:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for I was hungry, and you gave me food to eat. I was thirsty, and you gave me drink. I was a stranger, and you took\nme in. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 25:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I was naked, and you clothed me. I was sick, and you visited me. I was in prison, and you came to\nme.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 25:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen the righteous will answer him, saying, \u2018Lord, when did we see you hungry, and feed you; or thirsty, and give\nyou a drink? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 25:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When did we see you as a stranger, and take you in; or naked, and clothe you?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 25:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When did we see you sick, or in prison, and come to you?\u2019"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 25:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe King will answer them, \u2018Most certainly I tell you, because you did it to one of the least of these my\nbrothers,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:40 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here may be also correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or\n\u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["you did it to me.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 25:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then he will say also to those on the left hand, \u2018Depart from me, you cursed, into the eternal fire which is\nprepared for Iblis and his angels; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 25:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for I was hungry, and you didn\u2019t give me food to eat; I was thirsty, and you gave me no drink;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 25:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I was a stranger, and you didn\u2019t take me in; naked, and you didn\u2019t clothe me; sick, and in prison, and you didn\u2019t\nvisit me.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 25:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen they will also answer, saying, \u2018Lord, when did we see you hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or\nsick, or in prison, and didn\u2019t help you?\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 25:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThen he will answer them, saying, \u2018Most certainly I tell you, because you didn\u2019t do it to one of the least of\nthese, you didn\u2019t do it to me.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 25:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["These will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal\nlife.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 26:1"}, "When Isa had finished all these words, he said to his disciples,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 26:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou know that after two days the Passover is coming, and the Son of Man will be delivered up to be\ncrucified.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 26:3"}, "Then the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders of the people were gathered together in the court of the high priest,\nwho was called Caiaphas. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 26:4"}, "They took counsel together that they might take Isa by deceit, and kill him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 26:5"}, "But they said, \u201cNot during the feast, lest a riot occur amongst the people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 26:6"}, "Now when Isa was in Bethany, in the house of Shima\u2019un the leper,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 26:7"}, "a woman came to him having an alabaster jar of very expensive ointment, and she poured it on his head as he sat at the\ntable. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 26:8"}, "But when his disciples saw this, they were indignant, saying, \u201cWhy this waste?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 26:9"}, "For this ointment might have been sold for much, and given to the poor.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 26:10"}, "However, knowing this, Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you trouble the woman? She has done a good work for me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 26:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For you always have the poor with you; but you don\u2019t always have me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 26:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For in pouring this ointment on my body, she did it to prepare me for burial.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 26:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, wherever this Good News is preached in the whole world, what this woman has done will\nalso be spoken of as a memorial of her.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 26:14"}, "Then one of the twelve, who was called Yehuda Iscariot, went to the chief priests,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 26:15"}, "and said, \u201cWhat are you willing to give me, that I should deliver him to you?\u201d They weighed out for him thirty pieces of\nsilver. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 26:16"}, "From that time he sought opportunity to betray him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 26:17"}, "Now on the first day of unleavened bread, the disciples came to Isa, saying to him, \u201cWhere do you want us to prepare for\nyou to eat the Passover?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 26:18"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo into the city to a certain person, and tell him, \u2018The Teacher says, \u201cMy time is at hand. I will keep the\nPassover at your house with my disciples.\u201d\u2019\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 26:19"}, "The disciples did as Isa commanded them, and they prepared the Passover.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 26:20"}, "Now when evening had come, he was reclining at the table with the twelve disciples.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 26:21"}, "As they were eating, he said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you that one of you will betray\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 26:22"}, "They were exceedingly sorrowful, and each began to ask him, \u201cIt isn\u2019t me, is it, Lord?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 26:23"}, "He answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHe who dipped his hand with me in the dish will betray me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 26:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The Son of Man goes, even as it is written of him, but woe to that man through whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It\nwould be better for that man if he had not been born.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 26:25"}, "Yehuda, who betrayed him, answered, \u201cIt isn\u2019t me, is it, Rabbi?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou said it.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 26:26"}, "As they were eating, Isa took bread, gave thanks for", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["26:26\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cblessed\u201d instead of \u201cgave thanks for\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " it, and broke it. He gave to the disciples, and said,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake, eat; this is my body.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 26:27"}, "He took the cup, gave thanks, and gave to them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAll of you drink it,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 26:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for this is my blood of the new covenant, which is poured out for many for the remission of sins.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 26:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you that I will not drink of this fruit of the vine from now on, until that day when I drink it anew with\nyou in my Father\u2019s Kingdom.\u201d "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 26:30"}, "When they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 26:31"}, "Then Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAll of you will be made to stumble because of me tonight, for it is written, \u2018I will strike\nthe shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["26:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zakariya 13:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 26:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But after I am raised up, I will go before you into Galilee.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 26:33"}, "But Peter answered him, \u201cEven if all will be made to stumble because of you, I will never be made to stumble.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 26:34"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you that tonight, before the rooster crows, you will deny me three\ntimes.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 26:35"}, "Peter said to him, \u201cEven if I must die with you, I will not deny you.\u201d All of the disciples also said likewise.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 26:36"}, "Then Isa came with them to a place called Gethsemane, and said to his disciples,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSit here, while I go there and pray.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 26:37"}, "He took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and began to be sorrowful and severely troubled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 26:38"}, "Then he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy soul is exceedingly sorrowful, even to death. Stay here, and watch with\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 26:39"}, "He went forward a little, fell on his face, and prayed, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass away from me; nevertheless, not what I desire, but what you\ndesire.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 26:40"}, "He came to the disciples, and found them sleeping, and said to Peter,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat, couldn\u2019t you watch with me for one hour? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 26:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch and pray, that you don\u2019t enter into temptation. The spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is\nweak.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 26:42"}, "Again, a second time he went away, and prayed, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy Father, if this cup can\u2019t pass away from me unless I drink\nit, your desire be done.\u201d "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 26:43"}, "He came again and found them sleeping, for their eyes were heavy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 26:44"}, "He left them again, went away, and prayed a third time, saying the same words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 26:45"}, "Then he came to his disciples, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSleep on now, and take your rest. Behold, the hour is at hand, and\nthe Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 26:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Arise, let\u2019s be going. Behold, he who betrays me is at hand.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 26:47"}, "While he was still speaking, behold, Yehuda, one of the twelve, came, and with him a great multitude with swords and\nclubs, from the chief priests and elders of the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 26:48"}, "Now he who betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, \u201cWhoever I kiss, he is the one. Seize him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MAT 26:49"}, "Immediately he came to Isa, and said, \u201cHail, Rabbi!\u201d and kissed him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MAT 26:50"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFriend, why are you here?\u201d"]}, " Then they came and laid hands on Isa, and took him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MAT 26:51"}, "Behold, one of those who were with Isa stretched out his hand, and drew his sword, and struck the servant of the high\npriest, and struck off his ear. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MAT 26:52"}, "Then Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cPut your sword back into its place, for all those who take the sword will die by the sword.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "MAT 26:53"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Or do you think that I couldn\u2019t ask my Father, and he would even now send me more than twelve legions of angels?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "MAT 26:54"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["How then would the Scriptures be fulfilled that it must be so?\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "MAT 26:55"}, "In that hour Isa said to the multitudes, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHave you come out as against a robber with swords and clubs to seize me? I\nsat daily in the temple teaching, and you didn\u2019t arrest me. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "MAT 26:56"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But all this has happened that the Scriptures of the prophets might be\nfulfilled.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then all the disciples left him and fled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "MAT 26:57"}, "Those who had taken Isa led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were gathered\ntogether. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "MAT 26:58"}, "But Peter followed him from a distance, to the court of the high priest, and entered in and sat with the officers, to see\nthe end. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "MAT 26:59"}, "Now the chief priests, the elders, and the whole council sought false testimony against Isa, that they might put him to\ndeath; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "MAT 26:60"}, "and they found none. Even though many false witnesses came forward, they found none. But at last two false witnesses came\nforward, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "MAT 26:61"}, "and said, \u201cThis man said, \u2018I am able to destroy the temple of Allah, and to build it in three days.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "MAT 26:62"}, "The high priest stood up, and said to him, \u201cHave you no answer? What is this that these testify against you?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "MAT 26:63"}, "But Isa held his peace. The high priest answered him, \u201cI adjure you by the living Allah, that you tell us whether you are\nthe Masih, the Son of Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "MAT 26:64"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou have said it. Nevertheless, I tell you, after this you will see the Son of Man sitting at the\nright hand of Power, and coming on the clouds of the sky.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "MAT 26:65"}, "Then the high priest tore his clothing, saying, \u201cHe has spoken blasphemy! Why do we need any more witnesses? Behold, now\nyou have heard his blasphemy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "MAT 26:66"}, "What do you think?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered, \u201cHe is worthy of death!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "MAT 26:67"}, "Then they spat in his face and beat him with their fists, and some slapped him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "MAT 26:68"}, "saying, \u201cProphesy to us, you Masih! Who hit you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "69", "sid": "MAT 26:69"}, "Now Peter was sitting outside in the court, and a maid came to him, saying, \u201cYou were also with Isa, the Galilean!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "70", "sid": "MAT 26:70"}, "But he denied it before them all, saying, \u201cI don\u2019t know what you are talking about.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "71", "sid": "MAT 26:71"}, "When he had gone out onto the porch, someone else saw him, and said to those who were there, \u201cThis man also was with Isa\nof Nazareth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "72", "sid": "MAT 26:72"}, "Again he denied it with an oath, \u201cI don\u2019t know the man.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "73", "sid": "MAT 26:73"}, "After a little while those who stood by came and said to Peter, \u201cSurely you are also one of them, for your speech makes\nyou known.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "74", "sid": "MAT 26:74"}, "Then he began to curse and to swear, \u201cI don\u2019t know the man!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Immediately the rooster crowed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "75", "sid": "MAT 26:75"}, "Peter remembered the word which Isa had said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBefore the rooster crows, you will deny me three\ntimes.\u201d"]}, " Then he went out and wept bitterly. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 27:1"}, "Now when morning had come, all the chief priests and the elders of the people took counsel against Isa to put him to\ndeath: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 27:2"}, "and they bound him, and led him away, and delivered him up to Pontius Pilate, the governor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 27:3"}, "Then Yehuda, who betrayed him, when he saw that Isa was condemned, felt remorse, and brought back the thirty pieces of\nsilver to the chief priests and elders, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 27:4"}, "saying, \u201cI have sinned in that I betrayed innocent blood.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But they said, \u201cWhat is that to us? You see to it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 27:5"}, "He threw down the pieces of silver in the sanctuary, and departed. He went away and hanged himself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 27:6"}, "The chief priests took the pieces of silver, and said, \u201cIt\u2019s not lawful to put them into the treasury, since it is the\nprice of blood.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 27:7"}, "They took counsel, and bought the potter\u2019s field with them, to bury strangers in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 27:8"}, "Therefore that field was called \u201cThe Field of Blood\u201d to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 27:9"}, "Then that which was spoken through Jeremiah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["some manuscripts omit\n\u201cJeremiah\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " the prophet was fulfilled, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThey took the thirty pieces of silver, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the price of him upon whom a price had been set, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whom some of the children of Israel priced, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 27:10"}, "and they gave them for the potter\u2019s field, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as the Lord commanded me.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["27:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zakariya 11:12-13;\nJeremiah 19:1-13; 32:6-9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 27:11"}, "Now Isa stood before the governor: and the governor asked him, saying, \u201cAre you the King of the Jews?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSo you say.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 27:12"}, "When he was accused by the chief priests and elders, he answered nothing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 27:13"}, "Then Pilate said to him, \u201cDon\u2019t you hear how many things they testify against you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 27:14"}, "He gave him no answer, not even one word, so that the governor marvelled greatly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 27:15"}, "Now at the feast the governor was accustomed to release to the multitude one prisoner, whom they desired.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 27:16"}, "They had then a notable prisoner, called Barabbas. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 27:17"}, "When therefore they were gathered together, Pilate said to them, \u201cWhom do you want me to release to you? Barabbas, or\nIsa, who is called Masih?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 27:18"}, "For he knew that because of envy they had delivered him up.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 27:19"}, "While he was sitting on the judgement seat, his wife sent to him, saying, \u201cHave nothing to do with that righteous man,\nfor I have suffered many things today in a dream because of him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 27:20"}, "Now the chief priests and the elders persuaded the multitudes to ask for Barabbas, and destroy Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MAT 27:21"}, "But the governor answered them, \u201cWhich of the two do you want me to release to you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cBarabbas!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MAT 27:22"}, "Pilate said to them, \u201cWhat then shall I do to Isa, who is called Masih?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They all said to him, \u201cLet him be crucified!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MAT 27:23"}, "But the governor said, \u201cWhy? What evil has he done?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But they cried out exceedingly, saying, \u201cLet him be crucified!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MAT 27:24"}, "So when Pilate saw that nothing was being gained, but rather that a disturbance was starting, he took water, and washed\nhis hands before the multitude, saying, \u201cI am innocent of the blood of this righteous person. You see to it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MAT 27:25"}, "All the people answered, \u201cMay his blood be on us, and on our children!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MAT 27:26"}, "Then he released to them Barabbas, but Isa he flogged and delivered to be crucified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MAT 27:27"}, "Then the governor\u2019s soldiers took Isa into the Praetorium, and gathered the whole garrison together against him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 27:28"}, "They stripped him, and put a scarlet robe on him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MAT 27:29"}, "They braided a crown of thorns and put it on his head, and a reed in his right hand; and they knelt down before him, and\nmocked him, saying, \u201cHail, King of the Jews!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MAT 27:30"}, "They spat on him, and took the reed and struck him on the head.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MAT 27:31"}, "When they had mocked him, they took the robe off him, and put his clothes on him, and led him away to crucify him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MAT 27:32"}, "As they came out, they found a man of Cyrene, Shima\u2019un by name, and they compelled him to go with them, that he might\ncarry his cross. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MAT 27:33"}, "When they came to a place called \u201cGolgotha\u201d, that is to say, \u201cThe place of a skull,\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MAT 27:34"}, "they gave him sour wine", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, vinegar"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to drink mixed with\ngall.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Gall is a bitter-tasting, dark green oil from a wormwood plant that is alcoholic in its\neffect."]}], "caller": "+"}, " When he had tasted it, he would not drink. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MAT 27:35"}, "When they had crucified him, they divided his clothing amongst them, casting\nlots,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cthat it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet: \u2018They divided my garments amongst\nthem, and for my clothing they cast lots;\u2019\u201d [see Zabur 22:18 and\nYuhanna 19:24]"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MAT 27:36"}, "and they sat and watched him there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MAT 27:37"}, "They set up over his head the accusation against him written, \u201cTHIS IS JESUS, THE KING OF THE JEWS.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MAT 27:38"}, "Then there were two robbers crucified with him, one on his right hand and one on the left.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MAT 27:39"}, "Those who passed by blasphemed him, wagging their heads, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MAT 27:40"}, "and saying, \u201cYou who destroy the temple, and build it in three days, save yourself! If you are the Son of Allah, come\ndown from the cross!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MAT 27:41"}, "Likewise the chief priests also mocking, with the scribes, the\nPharisees,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:41 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201cthe Pharisees\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and the elders, said,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MAT 27:42"}, "\u201cHe saved others, but he can\u2019t save himself. If he is the King of Israel, let him come down from the cross now, and we\nwill believe in him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MAT 27:43"}, "He trusts in Allah. Let Allah deliver him now, if he wants him; for he said, \u2018I am the Son of Allah.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MAT 27:44"}, "The robbers also who were crucified with him cast on him the same reproach.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MAT 27:45"}, "Now from the sixth hour", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:45 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["noon"]}], "caller": "+"}, " there was darkness over all the land until the ninth\nhour.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:45 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MAT 27:46"}, "About the ninth hour Isa cried with a loud voice, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEli, Eli,\nlima"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:46 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201clama\u201d instead of \u201clima\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["sabachthani?\u201d "]}, " That is, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy Allah, my Allah, why have you forsaken\nme?\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["27:46 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 22:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MAT 27:47"}, "Some of them who stood there, when they heard it, said, \u201cThis man is calling Ilyas.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MAT 27:48"}, "Immediately one of them ran, and took a sponge, and filled it with vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave him a drink.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MAT 27:49"}, "The rest said, \u201cLet him be. Let\u2019s see whether Ilyas comes to save him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MAT 27:50"}, "Isa cried again with a loud voice, and yielded up his spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MAT 27:51"}, "Behold, the veil of the temple was torn in two from the top to the bottom. The earth quaked and the rocks were split.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MAT 27:52"}, "The tombs were opened, and many bodies of the saints who had fallen asleep were raised;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "MAT 27:53"}, "and coming out of the tombs after his resurrection, they entered into the holy city and appeared to many.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "MAT 27:54"}, "Now the centurion, and those who were with him watching Isa, when they saw the earthquake, and the things that were done,\nfeared exceedingly, saying, \u201cTruly this was the Son of Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "MAT 27:55"}, "Many women were there watching from afar, who had followed Isa from Galilee, serving him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "MAT 27:56"}, "Amongst them were Maryam Magdalene, Maryam the mother of Yaqub and Joses, and the mother of the sons of Zebedee.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "MAT 27:57"}, "When evening had come, a rich man from Arimathaea, named Yusuf, who himself was also Isa\u2019s disciple came.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "MAT 27:58"}, "This man went to Pilate, and asked for Isa\u2019s body. Then Pilate commanded the body to be given up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "MAT 27:59"}, "Yusuf took the body, and wrapped it in a clean linen cloth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "MAT 27:60"}, "and laid it in his own new tomb, which he had cut out in the rock, and he rolled a great stone against the door of the\ntomb, and departed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "MAT 27:61"}, "Maryam Magdalene was there, and the other Maryam, sitting opposite the tomb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "MAT 27:62"}, "Now on the next day, which was the day after the Preparation Day, the chief priests and the Pharisees were gathered\ntogether to Pilate, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "MAT 27:63"}, "saying, \u201cSir, we remember what that deceiver said while he was still alive: \u2018After three days I will rise again.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "MAT 27:64"}, "Command therefore that the tomb be made secure until the third day, lest perhaps his disciples come at night and steal\nhim away, and tell the people, \u2018He is risen from the dead;\u2019 and the last deception will be worse than the first.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "MAT 27:65"}, "Pilate said to them, \u201cYou have a guard. Go, make it as secure as you can.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "MAT 27:66"}, "So they went with the guard and made the tomb secure, sealing the stone.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "MAT 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MAT 28:1"}, "Now after the Sabbath, as it began to dawn on the first day of the week, Maryam Magdalene and the other Maryam came to see\nthe tomb. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MAT 28:2"}, "Behold, there was a great earthquake, for an angel of the Lord descended from the sky, and came and rolled away the stone\nfrom the door, and sat on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MAT 28:3"}, "His appearance was like lightning, and his clothing white as snow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MAT 28:4"}, "For fear of him, the guards shook, and became like dead men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MAT 28:5"}, "The angel answered the women, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, for I know that you seek Isa, who has been crucified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MAT 28:6"}, "He is not here, for he has risen, just like he said. Come, see the place where the Lord was lying.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MAT 28:7"}, "Go quickly and tell his disciples, \u2018He has risen from the dead, and behold, he goes before you into Galilee; there you\nwill see him.\u2019 Behold, I have told you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MAT 28:8"}, "They departed quickly from the tomb with fear and great joy, and ran to bring his disciples word.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MAT 28:9"}, "As they went to tell his disciples, behold, Isa met them, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cRejoice!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They came and took hold of his feet, and worshipped him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MAT 28:10"}, "Then Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid. Go tell my brothers\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here may be also correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or\n\u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["that they should go into Galilee, and there they will see\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MAT 28:11"}, "Now while they were going, behold, some of the guards came into the city, and told the chief priests all the things that\nhad happened. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MAT 28:12"}, "When they were assembled with the elders, and had taken counsel, they gave a large amount of silver to the soldiers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MAT 28:13"}, "saying, \u201cSay that his disciples came by night, and stole him away while we slept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MAT 28:14"}, "If this comes to the governor\u2019s ears, we will persuade him and make you free of worry.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MAT 28:15"}, "So they took the money and did as they were told. This saying was spread abroad amongst the Jews, and continues until\ntoday. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MAT 28:16"}, "But the eleven disciples went into Galilee, to the mountain where Isa had sent them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MAT 28:17"}, "When they saw him, they bowed down to him, but some doubted.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MAT 28:18"}, "Isa came to them and spoke to them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAll authority has been given to me in heaven and on earth.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MAT 28:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Go"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU add \u201ctherefore\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and make disciples of all nations, baptising them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MAT 28:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["teaching them to observe all things that I commanded you. Behold, I am with you always, even to the end of the\nage.\u201d"]}, " Amen. "]}]}